1
00:00:00,360 --> 00:00:02,680
-Hello? -I'm at the airport, brother.

2
00:00:02,800 --> 00:00:04,280
The lady didn’t get off the plane.

3
00:00:06,760 --> 00:00:08,360
Mercan’s phone is off…

4
00:00:09,240 --> 00:00:10,640
Ah!

5
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:13,600
- This is your doing, isn’t it?!
- What the hell are you talking about?

6
00:00:13,680 --> 00:00:14,960
She never got on the plane!

7
00:00:15,080 --> 00:00:16,616
What do you
mean she never got on the plane?

8
00:00:16,640 --> 00:00:19,240
Don’t
play dumb with me! Where did you take her?

9
00:00:19,440 --> 00:00:20,600
Have you lost your mind?

10
00:00:20,680 --> 00:00:24,000
Why would I kidnap her when she finally got
away from you!

11
00:00:24,080 --> 00:00:25,440
For God’s sake! Stop it!

12
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:27,320
With every passing second,

13
00:00:27,680 --> 00:00:29,840
she gets a little closer to death.

14
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:31,480
Aslı, she was already leaving.

15
00:00:31,560 --> 00:00:34,160
Why would you kidnap her and bring trouble
on yourself?

16
00:00:34,480 --> 00:00:35,920
She could’ve come back.

17
00:00:36,440 --> 00:00:37,920
She’s obsessed with Ateş.

18
00:00:38,400 --> 00:00:40,200
What the hell? You think this is a barn?

19
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:44,760
Where is Mercan?

20
00:00:45,720 --> 00:00:47,520
-Speak! -Let go!

21
00:00:49,320 --> 00:00:51,520
All
I wanted was for her to get away from you!

22
00:00:52,360 --> 00:00:53,840
Why would I stop her?

23
00:00:54,680 --> 00:00:57,480
They threatened me and took my taxi.

24
00:00:58,080 --> 00:00:59,560
I wanted to help the girl,

25
00:01:00,120 --> 00:01:01,520
but they held a gun to my head.

26
00:01:02,160 --> 00:01:04,160
They kidnapped Mercan
right under our noses.

27
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:08,040
Help!

28
00:01:08,760 --> 00:01:10,600
Why are you doing this?!

29
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:16,320
-Mercan. -Ateş.

30
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:22,720
Look, I’m here now. Don’t be scared.

31
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:27,360
I knew it… I knew you'd come.

32
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:30,320
Do whatever you want to me!

33
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:31,640
Let her go.

34
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:34,080
Let go of her. Let her go.

35
00:01:34,160 --> 00:01:35,440
Mercan, hold on.

36
00:01:35,520 --> 00:01:37,560
Hold on!

37
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:44,800
You won't get away this time.

38
00:01:46,280 --> 00:01:49,640
I'll never let anything happen to her.

39
00:02:58,640 --> 00:03:01,240
Mercan! Come
on, open your eyes. Open your eyes, Mercan.

40
00:03:01,480 --> 00:03:03,920
Come on. Mercan, open your eyes. Come on.

41
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:07,480
You can’t leave me! I won’t let you! You
hear me?!

42
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:12,080
Stay with me. Mercan! Mercan.

43
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:14,760
Come on, say something. Come on, baby.

44
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:20,080
Come on, love. Say something. Say something
to me. Come on Mercan!

45
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:24,480
Open your
eyes! Open your eyes, Mercan! Open!

46
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:30,160
Open your eyes. Come on, baby. Come on.

47
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:31,720
You cannot give up.

48
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:35,440
You're
so strong, Mercan. Open your eyes, Mercan.

49
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:37,800
Open your eyes, Mercan!

50
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:41,160
Open your eyes, already! Stay with me!

51
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:43,160
Stay with me, love.

52
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:50,440
Come on, breathe! You hear me?

53
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:52,720
Come on, love. Come on, Mercan.

54
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:55,880
Stay with
me, baby. Come on, open your eyes, already.

55
00:04:07,440 --> 00:04:11,560
That’s it… that’s it! You’re back.

56
00:04:11,640 --> 00:04:16,040
I told you that you're so strong, Mercan.
See, you're back. That's it. That's it.

57
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:21,200
See? See? You opened your eyes.

58
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:31,320
Come on, breathe. Breathe. Breathe, Mercan.

59
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:33,720
Keep breathing. You hear me?

60
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:38,400
You hear me? Don't give
up. Don't let go. You’re going to be okay.

61
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:40,720
You’re going to be okay. You hear me?

62
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:44,360
You hear me? Come on, baby.

63
00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:46,680
Come
on, open your eyes! Don’t you dare give up.

64
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:49,640
I won't let you go! Open your eyes, Mercan!

65
00:04:54,280 --> 00:04:57,480
That’s it… that’s it! You'll be alright.

66
00:04:57,560 --> 00:05:00,160
I’m getting you to the
hospital. You're going to be okay.

67
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:11,360
There’s no other way. You have to live.

68
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:16,920
There's no other way, Mercan.

69
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:51,560
No… no, no!
She’s alive? She survived again?

70
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:56,800
You idiot! Useless!

71
00:06:57,360 --> 00:07:00,640
You
failed! You couldn’t get rid of the snake!

72
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:33,200
Stay with me Mercan.

73
00:08:57,400 --> 00:09:01,200
Hey. Don’t wear yourself out talking.

74
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:08,840
You'll be fine. You'll recover.

75
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:12,520
We'll get to the hospital shortly.

76
00:09:13,960 --> 00:09:17,680
-Alright? -Yeah.

77
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:24,120
Seeing that beautiful smile of yours…

78
00:09:25,160 --> 00:09:27,040
that’s enough for me.

79
00:09:30,920 --> 00:09:33,880
-Are you alright? -Shh.

80
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:36,880
I am.

81
00:09:37,560 --> 00:09:43,120
If you’re okay, I’m okay.

82
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:51,640
You’re
breathing now. You’re okay… so I’m okay.

83
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:55,640
See, I'm breathing too.

84
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:58,120
Never again.

85
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:01,240
I’m never letting you go again.

86
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:05,400
Never.

87
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:08,680
I promise you. No
one… nothing… will ever separate us again.

88
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:19,480
You’re my whole world.

89
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:22,400
My Mercan.

90
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:28,560
I beg you. Don't ever leave me, please.

91
00:10:29,800 --> 00:10:31,480
Deal?

92
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:15,360
3 DAYS LATER

93
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:28,520
Anything from the camera we found?

94
00:12:29,360 --> 00:12:30,440
Nothing, so far.

95
00:12:30,520 --> 00:12:32,480
We
Couldn’t trace where the footage was sent.

96
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:35,000
Probably routed through a foreign IP.

97
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:38,960
They kidnapped my wife
in broad daylight and...

98
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:45,200
This isn’t normal. None of this is normal.

99
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:51,120
It’s not. Either a psychopath or
someone out for revenge.

100
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:53,960
That tattoo Mercan remembered might be the
key. We’ll find them.

101
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:56,880
I’m waiting on updates.
Something should come out of it.

102
00:12:58,160 --> 00:12:59,720
You’re carrying all the weight.

103
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:03,480
Man, please don't talk like that.

104
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:06,280
You take care of
Mercan. That’s what matters now.

105
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:08,440
How is she?

106
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:09,680
Better.

107
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:12,120
But the nightmares won’t leave her alone.

108
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:15,000
Not
easy, brother. She came back from the edge.

109
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:17,320
It’ll take time. Don't worry.

110
00:13:18,360 --> 00:13:20,480
This all happened because of me.

111
00:13:21,280 --> 00:13:24,400
If I hadn’t told
her to go, none of this would’ve happened.

112
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:27,080
I’ll never forgive myself.

113
00:13:27,720 --> 00:13:31,480
You’ve been torturing yourself for days.

114
00:13:31,760 --> 00:13:34,000
Would you want this happen to her?

115
00:13:34,080 --> 00:13:35,920
You wouldn't. So that’s the end of it.

116
00:13:37,440 --> 00:13:39,920
I should’ve known, Cemal. I should’ve.

117
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:43,280
But from now
on, I’m never letting her out of my sight.

118
00:13:43,480 --> 00:13:44,560
Never.

119
00:13:45,680 --> 00:13:48,600
Anyone who tries to hurt her will answer to
me.

120
00:13:50,840 --> 00:13:55,240
As long as
the people who tried to kill her walk free,

121
00:13:55,880 --> 00:13:57,000
I’ll never have peace.

122
00:13:58,200 --> 00:14:00,240
Not until I deal with them myself

123
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:02,120
I won’t rest.

124
00:14:02,920 --> 00:14:08,200
Don’t worry. I promise I’ll bring them to
you.

125
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:11,120
With any luck, this ends today.

126
00:14:11,520 --> 00:14:13,880
Mercan is about to wake
up. Talk to you later.

127
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:17,000
Good then. Stay safe, okay?

128
00:14:33,680 --> 00:14:35,000
Mercan.

129
00:14:42,240 --> 00:14:44,080
Mercan.

130
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:06,560
It's over. It's over.

131
00:15:12,640 --> 00:15:15,120
It's over.

132
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:18,360
I’m here. Look, we’re in our room.

133
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:21,480
It's a nightmare.

134
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:30,240
Don’t leave me.

135
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:33,520
I won’t.

136
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:35,640
From now on, I’ll always be right here.

137
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:38,440
Anyone who touches a
single hair on your head will answer to me.

138
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:40,120
Trust me.

139
00:15:40,720 --> 00:15:45,720
I trust you. Only you.

140
00:15:58,800 --> 00:16:00,680
I’m sorry…

141
00:16:02,040 --> 00:16:04,280
I keep bothering you with these nightmares…

142
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:08,160
Hey. What did we say?

143
00:16:08,320 --> 00:16:10,360
No apologizing for this.

144
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:16,200
Thank you.

145
00:16:17,120 --> 00:16:18,640
And no thanking me either.

146
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:21,800
You never listen.

147
00:16:23,520 --> 00:16:25,360
I guess I won’t listen on this one.

148
00:16:27,280 --> 00:16:29,160
Like you listen any other time…

149
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:37,280
If I’m still alive…

150
00:16:37,520 --> 00:16:40,080
if I’m still breathing… it’s because of
you.

151
00:16:41,920 --> 00:16:43,480
I’m glad you’re here.

152
00:16:47,040 --> 00:16:49,480
If only I could
tell you that you’re the reason I breathe.

153
00:16:50,120 --> 00:16:51,560
If only you knew

154
00:16:51,880 --> 00:16:54,080
that I exist because you exist.

155
00:16:59,480 --> 00:17:01,120
You too…

156
00:17:03,560 --> 00:17:05,160
I’m glad you’re alive.

157
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:13,880
I’m glad you’re here.

158
00:17:37,440 --> 00:17:39,560
Hey, what are you doing?

159
00:17:41,040 --> 00:17:43,080
Where to?

160
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:55,960
Come here.

161
00:18:00,480 --> 00:18:01,920
Slowly.

162
00:18:10,760 --> 00:18:14,400
I'm fine. Don't worry.

163
00:18:15,120 --> 00:18:16,760
Okay.

164
00:19:05,840 --> 00:19:07,840
You didn’t put anything on again.

165
00:19:08,720 --> 00:19:10,440
Thank you.

166
00:19:26,560 --> 00:19:28,640
It’s cold out. I don’t want you to freeze.

167
00:19:29,360 --> 00:19:30,880
Thank you.

168
00:19:31,560 --> 00:19:33,480
Come on, don’t stand here. You’ll get sick.

169
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:36,040
I'm not cold.

170
00:19:37,280 --> 00:19:39,000
Fresh air feels good.

171
00:19:39,360 --> 00:19:40,920
You’ll still get sick.

172
00:19:41,120 --> 00:19:44,520
I
Won't. Fresh air is good for me right now.

173
00:19:44,880 --> 00:19:46,400
But you’ll get cold.

174
00:19:47,800 --> 00:19:49,320
I won't.

175
00:19:51,680 --> 00:19:53,200
I'm not cold. See?

176
00:19:53,640 --> 00:19:55,080
I put this on.

177
00:19:56,360 --> 00:19:58,840
It’s thicker… I won’t be cold.

178
00:20:00,560 --> 00:20:02,320
I won't look after you if you get sick.

179
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:04,640
I know you will.

180
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:08,400
Or do you
want to get sick so I’ll take care of you?

181
00:20:10,120 --> 00:20:14,200
No... I just want to get some fresh air.

182
00:20:15,040 --> 00:20:16,800
I want to feel normal.

183
00:20:17,240 --> 00:20:19,720
I just want to sleep without nightmares.

184
00:20:21,320 --> 00:20:22,640
Is that too much to ask for?

185
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:25,320
No, it isn't.

186
00:20:27,640 --> 00:20:29,080
So… I can stay here?

187
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:32,200
Yeah, yeah.

188
00:20:32,960 --> 00:20:34,160
That’s right.

189
00:20:34,560 --> 00:20:36,920
You’ve got
to say “yeah” to me all the time.

190
00:20:47,360 --> 00:20:49,760
You’re probably not sleeping well because
of me.

191
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:52,760
Don't worry about me.

192
00:20:53,760 --> 00:20:55,680
Just focus on getting better.

193
00:20:57,480 --> 00:21:00,080
I want to be free of these nightmares.

194
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:06,920
I was like this when I was a child.

195
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:09,920
Even the slightest thing would affect me.

196
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:12,560
The same nightmare, over and over…

197
00:21:13,840 --> 00:21:16,160
I still see it.

198
00:21:17,040 --> 00:21:20,080
Someone’s pain‑filled scream rises…

199
00:21:20,880 --> 00:21:22,720
…out of the darkness.

200
00:21:23,120 --> 00:21:24,800
I never see who it is.

201
00:21:25,720 --> 00:21:28,560
I only hear the scream.

202
00:21:30,800 --> 00:21:34,800
It’s so frightening.
It sounds like children’s voices.

203
00:21:38,480 --> 00:21:40,240
It'll pass. Don't worry.

204
00:21:40,520 --> 00:21:42,000
Only time...

205
00:21:42,960 --> 00:21:45,120
How can you be so sure?

206
00:21:45,440 --> 00:21:47,360
Did your pain ever pass?

207
00:21:54,080 --> 00:21:55,920
Did you ever escape your nightmares?

208
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:07,640
Time teaches you how to live with them.

209
00:22:11,680 --> 00:22:13,240
I'll learn that too.

210
00:22:13,360 --> 00:22:16,640
I won’t let what I lived take over my life.

211
00:22:18,800 --> 00:22:20,600
I don’t doubt that for a second.

212
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:23,480
Let's go inside. Time to sleep.

213
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:26,480
- We were good here.
- I don’t want any objections.

214
00:22:27,520 --> 00:22:29,080
Okay.

215
00:22:31,560 --> 00:22:33,120
Come on.

216
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:46,720
Slowly.

217
00:22:56,440 --> 00:22:58,040
Is this okay? Are you comfortable?

218
00:22:59,360 --> 00:23:00,720
Yes.

219
00:23:10,240 --> 00:23:13,120
-Goodnight. -Goodnight.

220
00:23:22,720 --> 00:23:24,080
Don't be scared.

221
00:23:30,160 --> 00:23:31,480
I'm right here.

222
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:38,680
Try to sleep now.

223
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:08,400
My baby,

224
00:24:26,240 --> 00:24:28,520
what would I have
done if something happened to you?

225
00:24:49,080 --> 00:24:50,760
How innocent you are.

226
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:14,240
Good morning.

227
00:25:16,040 --> 00:25:17,360
Good morning.

228
00:25:18,840 --> 00:25:20,200
Didn't you sleep at all?

229
00:25:21,680 --> 00:25:23,800
- But you stayed awake.
- What did I tell you?

230
00:25:27,680 --> 00:25:32,360
You told me to stop worrying about you.

231
00:25:34,800 --> 00:25:36,200
How do you feel?

232
00:25:38,320 --> 00:25:39,800
I'm fine.

233
00:25:44,920 --> 00:25:47,120
Shall we
walk in the garden before breakfast?

234
00:25:49,360 --> 00:25:50,840
If you want to, go.

235
00:25:52,600 --> 00:25:54,720
I'd better stay in the room.

236
00:25:58,920 --> 00:26:01,000
What scares you isn’t outside…

237
00:26:02,280 --> 00:26:03,720
…it’s in your head.

238
00:26:08,160 --> 00:26:11,960
Also, when I'm with you,
you shouldn't worry about anything.

239
00:26:18,040 --> 00:26:20,840
You know that I will protect
you, even at the cost of my life.

240
00:26:23,680 --> 00:26:25,840
I know.

241
00:26:27,320 --> 00:26:28,920
I learned that by living it.

242
00:26:31,080 --> 00:26:32,480
Then let’s go. Come on.

243
00:26:49,600 --> 00:26:51,880
Okay, let's go.

244
00:26:52,080 --> 00:26:54,280
-Let me wash my face. -Okay.

245
00:27:21,680 --> 00:27:23,360
I’ll find the ones who did this to you.

246
00:27:30,640 --> 00:27:35,200
Mom, please! Why are you doing this?

247
00:27:35,920 --> 00:27:37,920
You haven’t said a word in days!

248
00:27:38,640 --> 00:27:41,080
You won’t even let me explain!

249
00:27:41,160 --> 00:27:42,640
Explain what?

250
00:27:42,800 --> 00:27:45,800
You've been wandering around me for days. I
saw what I needed to see.

251
00:27:46,240 --> 00:27:48,720
But it hurts me…

252
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:51,800
Good! I was hurt too. Now it’s your turn.

253
00:27:53,840 --> 00:27:56,800
Mom… I didn’t do anything wrong!

254
00:27:57,200 --> 00:27:59,800
Malik loves me. And I love him!

255
00:28:00,880 --> 00:28:02,320
Quiet, Çiçek! Quiet!

256
00:28:04,400 --> 00:28:05,840
Why should I be quiet?

257
00:28:05,920 --> 00:28:08,240
What’s wrong with loving someone? Is love
a crime?

258
00:28:08,320 --> 00:28:09,840
It is! It is a crime!

259
00:28:10,600 --> 00:28:15,960
You and Malik tricked
me… lied to me… went behind my back! Crime!

260
00:28:17,320 --> 00:28:20,960
As long
as I live, this marriage will never happen!

261
00:28:24,480 --> 00:28:28,240
I wish I had died before seeing this day.

262
00:28:36,400 --> 00:28:38,800
Did I raise you to be like this?!

263
00:28:39,840 --> 00:28:43,120
Look into my eyes, Çiçek!
Did I raise you to be like this?!

264
00:28:45,480 --> 00:28:48,160
I found out my daughter was getting married
from strangers.

265
00:28:48,800 --> 00:28:50,360
If it weren’t for Zehra...

266
00:28:53,400 --> 00:28:55,600
I knew it was her.

267
00:28:56,040 --> 00:28:57,880
Don’t talk about Zehra! Mind yourself.

268
00:28:58,040 --> 00:29:01,040
You betrayed
your own mother for a man you barely know!

269
00:29:01,680 --> 00:29:04,920
Mom, what "barely know"? Malik is Malik.

270
00:29:05,320 --> 00:29:08,680
You loved him too. What changed?

271
00:29:08,760 --> 00:29:10,960
I don’t love him anymore!

272
00:29:12,080 --> 00:29:14,480
And I told you the other day, Çiçek...

273
00:29:14,600 --> 00:29:16,600
Don’t let your brother hear about this.

274
00:29:16,840 --> 00:29:20,200
I won’t have him
dragged into trouble because of you.

275
00:29:21,560 --> 00:29:25,880
Now move. I've got work to do.

276
00:29:27,560 --> 00:29:28,720
Malik… honestly.

277
00:29:29,360 --> 00:29:32,280
You'll
face the consequences if you see him again.

278
00:29:32,800 --> 00:29:34,560
Go away, Çiçek. I don't want to see you.

279
00:29:40,560 --> 00:29:42,000
Shame on you.

280
00:29:49,720 --> 00:29:51,320
You had one job!

281
00:29:51,520 --> 00:29:53,480
And you messed up everything.

282
00:29:53,920 --> 00:29:55,440
Don’t blame me.

283
00:29:55,680 --> 00:29:57,600
You’re the one who wanted her to suffer

284
00:29:57,680 --> 00:30:00,120
instead of ending it with a single bullet.

285
00:30:01,120 --> 00:30:03,640
How was I
supposed to know you’d be this incompetent?

286
00:30:04,480 --> 00:30:06,080
Stop talking and listen.

287
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:07,920
Ateş Karahan is on my tail.

288
00:30:08,120 --> 00:30:10,880
You’re going to get me a million dollars so
I can disappear.

289
00:30:10,960 --> 00:30:13,720
What? A million dollars?

290
00:30:15,400 --> 00:30:18,560
Are
you insane? How am I supposed to find that?

291
00:30:19,480 --> 00:30:20,800
Not my problem.

292
00:30:20,920 --> 00:30:22,920
I told you
from the start, this job was risky.

293
00:30:23,720 --> 00:30:25,440
If you don’t want me getting caught

294
00:30:25,520 --> 00:30:27,320
and ratting you out, you’ll pay that money.

295
00:30:27,400 --> 00:30:29,240
If
I get caught, I’ll take you down with me.

296
00:30:31,600 --> 00:30:33,160
Listen...

297
00:30:33,560 --> 00:30:35,320
I'm hanging up now.

298
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:38,960
I’ll text you
the time and place you'll bring the money.

299
00:30:47,640 --> 00:30:49,240
What am I going to do now?

300
00:30:50,200 --> 00:30:51,760
He’s lost his mind.

301
00:31:01,640 --> 00:31:03,240
You idiot.

302
00:31:08,960 --> 00:31:12,880
That’s what happens when
you act with no knowledge.

303
00:31:15,640 --> 00:31:18,320
I thought of everything!

304
00:31:19,360 --> 00:31:20,920
I picked Reşat on purpose,

305
00:31:24,560 --> 00:31:27,960
so if he got caught, it would lead back to
Haydar.

306
00:31:33,240 --> 00:31:37,520
I planned everything…
except Ateş’s stubbornness.

307
00:31:42,440 --> 00:31:44,000
And what good did it do?

308
00:31:44,960 --> 00:31:47,160
Ateş is even
more attached to that little snake now.

309
00:31:47,240 --> 00:31:49,600
He cares about her deeply.

310
00:31:49,680 --> 00:31:51,640
I know, mother...

311
00:31:51,720 --> 00:31:53,560
just tell me what we’re going to do.

312
00:31:54,920 --> 00:31:56,680
We’ll get rid of Mercan...

313
00:31:57,320 --> 00:31:59,000
but my way.

314
00:32:04,120 --> 00:32:06,240
First we deal with this man…

315
00:32:06,560 --> 00:32:08,200
before he becomes a bigger problem.

316
00:32:18,200 --> 00:32:20,880
Thank God,
Mercan is getting better every day.

317
00:32:22,720 --> 00:32:25,840
If only she’d leave her room. She’s shut
herself in completely.

318
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:28,320
She’ll recover.

319
00:32:28,800 --> 00:32:31,400
And to be fair, Ateş is
taking good care of her.

320
00:32:32,240 --> 00:32:34,000
He doesn’t leave her side.

321
00:32:36,680 --> 00:32:39,000
He took her under his wing.

322
00:32:39,800 --> 00:32:41,640
He’s protecting her like she’s precious.

323
00:32:41,880 --> 00:32:44,240
How
do you know he didn’t kidnap her himself?

324
00:32:46,280 --> 00:32:48,560
Maybe he did it to get back at me.

325
00:32:52,080 --> 00:32:54,520
Then he regretted it.

326
00:32:58,800 --> 00:33:00,680
I don’t believe that.

327
00:33:01,040 --> 00:33:02,960
Ateş isn’t that kind of man.

328
00:33:04,320 --> 00:33:07,080
What do you know about him?

329
00:33:10,880 --> 00:33:13,640
I’ve said it from the
start there’s something off about that man.

330
00:33:15,520 --> 00:33:17,920
And it’s time to put an end to this.

331
00:33:21,720 --> 00:33:23,440
Long past time.

332
00:33:23,600 --> 00:33:25,360
What are you planning, Haydar?

333
00:33:26,640 --> 00:33:28,320
I’m gathering my old friends.

334
00:33:29,280 --> 00:33:32,400
Even if the partnership
with Nezir doesn’t bring much, it’s steady.

335
00:33:32,680 --> 00:33:35,160
The scent of money will bring them back.

336
00:33:36,840 --> 00:33:38,320
I’ll have to build my army first.

337
00:33:57,120 --> 00:33:58,920
Where the hell are you?

338
00:34:00,240 --> 00:34:01,720
Who are you calling, Haydar?

339
00:34:04,080 --> 00:34:07,400
Ziya. He’s well‑connected.

340
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:10,600
From now on, I'll think
big and play big, Nermin.

341
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:13,680
Not only will I go after Ateş,

342
00:34:13,960 --> 00:34:16,880
I’ve put his whole family under my radar.

343
00:34:20,160 --> 00:34:22,000
Go after all of them

344
00:34:24,680 --> 00:34:26,720
but leave Müzeyyen to me.

345
00:34:27,520 --> 00:34:31,360
When
the time comes, I'll put her in her place.

346
00:34:32,160 --> 00:34:35,320
I’ll
make her regret everything she’s ever done.

347
00:34:37,960 --> 00:34:39,360
As you wish.

348
00:34:40,360 --> 00:34:41,960
A big war is coming.

349
00:34:43,640 --> 00:34:45,600
Get ready.

350
00:34:59,040 --> 00:35:00,480
Come on, put your coat on.

351
00:35:05,640 --> 00:35:07,840
You
should take yours too. It’s cold outside.

352
00:35:09,720 --> 00:35:10,760
I’m fine.

353
00:35:40,800 --> 00:35:43,960
You’re
saying that? You’re the one dressed thin.

354
00:35:51,760 --> 00:35:53,200
…Let’s go.

355
00:36:03,360 --> 00:36:06,320
I guess Mercan won’t
be coming down for breakfast today either.

356
00:36:06,880 --> 00:36:08,600
Yeah, looks like it.

357
00:36:09,240 --> 00:36:12,200
She’ll have breakfast
alone with her husband.

358
00:36:14,880 --> 00:36:16,920
She won't let me swallow a bite now.

359
00:36:24,240 --> 00:36:25,760
Where are Ateş and Cemal?

360
00:36:26,400 --> 00:36:28,240
Mr. Cemal left early.

361
00:36:28,760 --> 00:36:31,200
And Mr. Ateş
said he wouldn’t be coming to breakfast.

362
00:36:32,200 --> 00:36:34,280
He went out to the garden with Mrs. Mercan.

363
00:36:44,960 --> 00:36:46,720
Ateş was never like this.

364
00:36:47,200 --> 00:36:50,760
Sitting
at the table with family was sacred to him.

365
00:36:54,200 --> 00:36:56,360
That girl changed my son completely.

366
00:36:57,920 --> 00:36:59,480
What do you expect?

367
00:36:59,960 --> 00:37:03,000
Well, she is his wife. Of course he’ll have
breakfast with her.

368
00:37:09,800 --> 00:37:13,880
You’ll be sitting alone at that table for
a long time.

369
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:21,400
I’ve lost my appetite, Haydar.

370
00:37:22,280 --> 00:37:24,120
I’ll go out to the garden and walk a bit.

371
00:37:30,080 --> 00:37:33,240
-Wait, let's go together. -That’d be good.

372
00:37:34,880 --> 00:37:37,960
We can finally have a
peaceful family breakfast.

373
00:38:32,200 --> 00:38:35,120
Aren’t you going to get cold? I’m fine.

374
00:38:36,080 --> 00:38:37,920
No.

375
00:38:42,240 --> 00:38:43,760
Now I feel better.

376
00:39:00,520 --> 00:39:03,800
You’re such a bookworm. I noticed.

377
00:39:05,160 --> 00:39:06,760
You finished another book last night.

378
00:39:08,920 --> 00:39:10,400
I missed reading.

379
00:39:11,040 --> 00:39:12,760
I hadn’t had the chance in a long time…

380
00:39:13,760 --> 00:39:15,760
And now that I’m left with nothing to do…

381
00:39:16,880 --> 00:39:18,200
Do you read?

382
00:39:19,360 --> 00:39:22,000
I do. Just… can’t focus lately.

383
00:39:23,960 --> 00:39:27,760
My favorite excuse. I use it all the time.

384
00:39:33,240 --> 00:39:34,440
What was that sound?

385
00:39:35,760 --> 00:39:38,120
Hey, hey… nothing. Just a cute cat.

386
00:39:38,320 --> 00:39:40,600
See, it got scared and ran away.

387
00:39:46,000 --> 00:39:48,760
I hate that I can’t shake this feeling.

388
00:39:50,360 --> 00:39:52,000
Don’t judge yourself so harshly.

389
00:39:53,320 --> 00:39:57,080
Fear keeps you alive sometimes.

390
00:39:58,760 --> 00:40:02,480
Sometimes… but not always.
It becomes bothering if it is always.

391
00:40:03,560 --> 00:40:05,480
I’m not usually this scared.

392
00:40:07,160 --> 00:40:08,760
Oh, I know.

393
00:40:09,400 --> 00:40:11,880
You chased
me all the way out there to punch someone.

394
00:40:16,440 --> 00:40:19,160
I don’t want to give in to fear.

395
00:40:20,560 --> 00:40:25,120
That’s exactly what they wanted. I won’t
let them win.

396
00:40:29,520 --> 00:40:31,320
Then don’t.

397
00:40:34,200 --> 00:40:35,960
Don’t fight yourself.

398
00:40:37,600 --> 00:40:40,080
Let yourself feel what you feel.

399
00:40:45,040 --> 00:40:46,880
Don't judge your feelings any more.

400
00:40:48,000 --> 00:40:49,800
Give it time.

401
00:40:51,280 --> 00:40:53,600
I feel secure only when I'm with you.

402
00:41:02,520 --> 00:41:05,560
I want to know why, and who did this to me.

403
00:41:11,160 --> 00:41:15,080
Mercan! Dear.

404
00:41:15,600 --> 00:41:17,480
Finally outside.

405
00:41:18,320 --> 00:41:19,920
You look better.

406
00:41:21,520 --> 00:41:24,200
I am. We were just sitting.

407
00:41:25,640 --> 00:41:27,200
How nice. How nice.

408
00:41:28,200 --> 00:41:29,560
It’s cold out, dear.

409
00:41:30,200 --> 00:41:32,760
Don’t stay out too long. Your kidneys are
sensitive.

410
00:41:35,480 --> 00:41:37,920
You’re taking your meds, right?

411
00:41:39,040 --> 00:41:41,000
-Yeah, I am. -Good.

412
00:41:41,560 --> 00:41:42,800
Don't worry.

413
00:41:44,160 --> 00:41:47,720
You heard what the doctor said. You need to
take care of yourself.

414
00:41:52,400 --> 00:41:56,040
Ateş, she doesn’t listen.

415
00:41:56,760 --> 00:41:58,360
Please take good care of her.

416
00:42:07,080 --> 00:42:10,160
Any leads on who did it?

417
00:42:11,640 --> 00:42:13,240
You’ll know when we find out.

418
00:42:15,640 --> 00:42:19,000
Funny… I couldn’t find anything either.

419
00:42:22,200 --> 00:42:26,960
Maybe I'm looking too far. Maybe
the culprit is right under my nose.

420
00:42:35,520 --> 00:42:37,200
Kidnapping someone,

421
00:42:38,080 --> 00:42:41,720
especially a woman, sounds more like
your style than mine.

422
00:42:48,360 --> 00:42:51,720
The only reason
I’m not doing anything right now is Mercan.

423
00:42:59,520 --> 00:43:00,720
Please…

424
00:43:04,000 --> 00:43:05,880
And Dad, don’t accuse him.

425
00:43:06,480 --> 00:43:08,120
If it weren’t for him, I’d be dead.

426
00:43:15,760 --> 00:43:18,960
Come on. Let's go.

427
00:43:37,040 --> 00:43:38,520
Come on, let’s walk a bit.

428
00:44:37,640 --> 00:44:39,400
Ouch...

429
00:44:52,440 --> 00:44:53,800
Mom...

430
00:44:56,960 --> 00:44:59,600
Why won’t you let me marry Malik?

431
00:45:00,040 --> 00:45:02,120
What has he ever done to you?

432
00:45:03,840 --> 00:45:05,520
Oh, not this again.

433
00:45:07,120 --> 00:45:08,600
Yes, again.

434
00:45:11,440 --> 00:45:14,920
I said no. And no means no.

435
00:45:18,120 --> 00:45:22,320
What if he decides to take you back to his
hometown one day?

436
00:45:23,040 --> 00:45:24,920
Is that your only issue, Mom?

437
00:45:25,400 --> 00:45:27,000
He doesn’t have such a plan.

438
00:45:27,400 --> 00:45:28,880
Not now.

439
00:45:29,240 --> 00:45:32,560
What if he
takes you away later on? Then what?

440
00:45:32,680 --> 00:45:35,560
I’m not giving my daughter away
to some far off place.

441
00:45:38,200 --> 00:45:40,200
You followed Dad for love.

442
00:45:44,320 --> 00:45:46,760
You did it knowing you wouldn’t be happy.

443
00:45:51,560 --> 00:45:53,000
And look how that ended.

444
00:45:55,200 --> 00:45:58,840
Just because he left us
doesn’t mean everyone will.

445
00:45:59,400 --> 00:46:01,120
That’s unfair.

446
00:46:01,640 --> 00:46:03,160
Maybe.

447
00:46:03,760 --> 00:46:05,840
But I suffered. You won’t.

448
00:46:06,840 --> 00:46:08,480
That's my final word.

449
00:46:11,040 --> 00:46:12,680
I’m not a child, Mother.

450
00:46:14,120 --> 00:46:16,040
I can make my own decisions.

451
00:46:16,920 --> 00:46:21,400
I love him, and I want your approval.

452
00:46:23,960 --> 00:46:25,920
You won’t get it. Ever.

453
00:46:35,760 --> 00:46:37,080
My beauties?

454
00:46:39,080 --> 00:46:41,040
What’s going on here? Are you two arguing?

455
00:46:42,280 --> 00:46:46,040
Your sister bought stringy beans.

456
00:46:46,200 --> 00:46:47,560
I was scolding her.

457
00:46:51,760 --> 00:46:53,120
Stringy beans?

458
00:46:57,680 --> 00:46:59,120
So, this is your only problem?

459
00:47:20,680 --> 00:47:23,280
You did all this for us?
When did you prepare everything?

460
00:47:24,560 --> 00:47:28,720
I didn’t. I
asked Çiçek while you were in the bathroom.

461
00:47:31,000 --> 00:47:33,080
Thank you. It looks beautiful.

462
00:47:33,880 --> 00:47:35,440
Even the flowers…

463
00:47:37,240 --> 00:47:38,920
That wasn’t me.

464
00:47:39,000 --> 00:47:40,720
Probably Çiçek.

465
00:47:43,400 --> 00:47:45,040
You’re not cold, right?

466
00:47:47,240 --> 00:47:49,000
I’m fine.

467
00:48:02,760 --> 00:48:04,640
Were you always this gentle?

468
00:48:05,800 --> 00:48:07,560
I’m almost glad they kidnapped me.

469
00:48:09,800 --> 00:48:11,040
You’re getting spoiled again.

470
00:48:12,120 --> 00:48:13,680
Not true.

471
00:48:19,000 --> 00:48:21,520
Eat before your omelet gets cold.

472
00:48:31,680 --> 00:48:35,280
Mmm... it’s delicious.

473
00:48:40,560 --> 00:48:42,200
You eat too. Here.

474
00:49:03,080 --> 00:49:04,600
Not bad.

475
00:49:14,840 --> 00:49:17,280
Here. Taste this also.

476
00:49:26,520 --> 00:49:27,840
Thank you.

477
00:49:29,480 --> 00:49:31,240
Are you going to thank me for everything?

478
00:49:34,480 --> 00:49:36,040
Should I say "thanks" instead?

479
00:49:37,920 --> 00:49:39,720
But you eat too.

480
00:49:40,640 --> 00:49:42,120
Don’t worry about me.

481
00:49:45,040 --> 00:49:46,640
But I want to worry about you.

482
00:49:59,320 --> 00:50:00,360
Here.

483
00:50:16,400 --> 00:50:17,720
Ateş?

484
00:50:18,680 --> 00:50:22,320
We have a meeting at 11.
And you’re here having breakfast?

485
00:50:25,200 --> 00:50:27,000
There’s no meeting. I postponed it.

486
00:50:28,720 --> 00:50:30,400
But it’s an important deal.

487
00:50:31,200 --> 00:50:33,680
How could you postpone it when we were just
about to sign?

488
00:50:33,760 --> 00:50:36,120
I postponed it. That’s my call.

489
00:50:43,960 --> 00:50:45,880
My priorities are different right now.

490
00:50:54,960 --> 00:50:59,760
Fine. Enjoy, then.

491
00:51:05,880 --> 00:51:09,520
You should’ve gone. You
don’t have to babysit me.

492
00:51:09,880 --> 00:51:11,640
Now I feel bad.

493
00:51:13,560 --> 00:51:15,440
You shouldn't.

494
00:51:17,160 --> 00:51:18,480
I’m exactly where I want to be.

495
00:51:30,400 --> 00:51:32,240
You’re really spoiled today.

496
00:51:33,200 --> 00:51:36,200
What can I
do? Yours looked better… I couldn’t resist.

497
00:51:40,560 --> 00:51:42,680
Alright. Don’t forget the favor I did you.

498
00:51:43,600 --> 00:51:45,120
It won't happen a second time.

499
00:51:51,720 --> 00:51:54,600
Finish your breakfast.
You’ll miss your medication time.

500
00:51:55,520 --> 00:51:57,280
Yes, sir.

501
00:51:58,520 --> 00:52:01,320
Good girl. Stay like this always.

502
00:52:02,520 --> 00:52:04,040
Don’t get too excited.

503
00:52:04,840 --> 00:52:07,440
Might be the last time.

504
00:52:08,600 --> 00:52:10,080
You were just getting started.

505
00:52:11,520 --> 00:52:13,360
Old habits die hard.

506
00:52:16,600 --> 00:52:19,800
Come on. Don't let your omelet get
cold. You haven't taken a bite yet.

507
00:52:28,440 --> 00:52:30,560
Welcome, come in.

508
00:52:31,000 --> 00:52:33,480
I told Çiçek to let Mercan
and Ateş know you're here.

509
00:52:33,960 --> 00:52:34,960
Please, come in.

510
00:52:37,520 --> 00:52:38,720
Hello.

511
00:52:39,000 --> 00:52:40,360
Welcome. Please sit.

512
00:52:41,000 --> 00:52:42,600
-Mr. Haydar. -Welcome.

513
00:52:42,880 --> 00:52:44,880
-Hello. -Welcome.

514
00:52:46,400 --> 00:52:47,680
Please have a seat.

515
00:52:53,000 --> 00:52:58,800
So, how are you Mrs.
Nermin? You look lovely as always, Nermin.

516
00:52:59,240 --> 00:53:03,080
Thank you, Yaşar. You're polite as always.

517
00:53:06,640 --> 00:53:08,120
Your home is beautiful.

518
00:53:08,800 --> 00:53:11,720
I had
seen the outside but inside is much nicer.

519
00:53:13,040 --> 00:53:14,680
That's right. Right.

520
00:53:15,200 --> 00:53:17,040
It wasn’t like this when we bought it.

521
00:53:17,360 --> 00:53:19,520
I fixed everything myself.

522
00:53:20,320 --> 00:53:21,760
I see.

523
00:53:22,080 --> 00:53:24,200
You haven’t been at the company lately.

524
00:53:27,160 --> 00:53:29,280
No need. Mercan handles things.

525
00:53:35,040 --> 00:53:37,160
You are Mr. Ateş's staff, right?

526
00:53:38,240 --> 00:53:39,760
You're very quiet.

527
00:53:40,920 --> 00:53:44,280
Are you waiting for Mr. Ateş
to arrive and give you permission to talk?

528
00:53:45,360 --> 00:53:47,400
That's right. I'm Mr. Ateş's staff.

529
00:53:48,120 --> 00:53:50,560
But that’s not why I’m quiet.

530
00:53:50,960 --> 00:53:55,160
I don’t like pointless chatter. That might
be it.

531
00:53:59,080 --> 00:54:00,840
Mr. Haydar, I wanted to talk to you...

532
00:54:00,920 --> 00:54:04,280
-Shall we go, dear? -Yes.

533
00:54:18,880 --> 00:54:21,280
- What a lovely surprise. Welcome.
- Thank you.

534
00:54:21,360 --> 00:54:22,720
Get well soon, Mrs. Mercan.

535
00:54:22,840 --> 00:54:24,400
-Thank you. -Get well soon.

536
00:54:24,480 --> 00:54:26,000
-Get well soon. -Get well soon.

537
00:54:26,080 --> 00:54:27,240
Thank you.

538
00:54:28,360 --> 00:54:29,960
It's great to see you all here.

539
00:54:30,320 --> 00:54:32,120
Great to see you too, Mrs Mercan.

540
00:54:32,480 --> 00:54:33,840
I’m so glad you recovered.

541
00:54:34,360 --> 00:54:35,440
Thank you.

542
00:54:35,560 --> 00:54:37,400
You look much better now.

543
00:54:40,880 --> 00:54:42,360
You're good. You're good.

544
00:54:46,000 --> 00:54:47,880
-Hello. -Hi.

545
00:54:48,040 --> 00:54:49,880
Demet, I’m glad you all came.

546
00:54:50,160 --> 00:54:51,880
ANLAYAMADIM.

547
00:54:52,320 --> 00:54:54,160
-Mercan. -Welcome, Demet.

548
00:54:57,520 --> 00:54:59,120
-Nice to see you.

549
00:55:07,120 --> 00:55:09,520
You’re here too?

550
00:55:10,360 --> 00:55:11,680
Yes we are.

551
00:55:11,760 --> 00:55:14,160
Whoa, everyone's here.

552
00:55:15,160 --> 00:55:18,560
See?
How precious you are to all of us, Mercan.

553
00:55:21,560 --> 00:55:23,480
We were terrified that day.

554
00:55:23,680 --> 00:55:26,120
God protected you and spared you for us.

555
00:55:42,320 --> 00:55:44,520
I signed the documents, Zahide.

556
00:55:45,120 --> 00:55:46,480
Pick them up before you leave.

557
00:55:46,560 --> 00:55:50,440
Of course, Mr. Ateş. We
handled the meetings you skipped.

558
00:55:52,520 --> 00:55:53,960
How’s work?

559
00:55:54,040 --> 00:55:56,360
Ms. Zahide is helping me a lot. Thank you.

560
00:55:57,200 --> 00:55:59,200
I want you to work in every department.

561
00:56:00,600 --> 00:56:02,320
Learn the whole system.

562
00:56:02,480 --> 00:56:04,000
Sure. Don't worry.

563
00:56:04,720 --> 00:56:08,120
- Let me tell Çiçek to bring something.
- Sit.

564
00:56:10,200 --> 00:56:11,800
She’ll come.

565
00:56:15,680 --> 00:56:17,680
Please, have a seat.

566
00:56:27,560 --> 00:56:31,560
Mrs. Mercan,
now I understand why you recovered so fast.

567
00:56:34,480 --> 00:56:36,600
Mr. Ateş takes good care of you.

568
00:56:43,600 --> 00:56:49,120
Um,
I mean... you took good rest. That's why...

569
00:56:54,000 --> 00:56:56,000
No, you're right.

570
00:57:00,800 --> 00:57:02,400
I owe him my life.

571
00:57:12,680 --> 00:57:16,320
If it weren’t for
him, maybe right now I would’ve…

572
00:57:35,600 --> 00:57:39,080
I’ll take the snacks.
You take these drinks.

573
00:57:42,880 --> 00:57:44,880
Are you insane? What are you doing?

574
00:57:46,120 --> 00:57:47,800
Why did you run to my mother?

575
00:57:48,440 --> 00:57:51,400
What’s your problem? What do you want from
us?

576
00:57:51,640 --> 00:57:53,640
Look at the crazy one getting offended!

577
00:57:54,000 --> 00:57:55,960
How was I supposed to know she didn’t know?

578
00:57:56,040 --> 00:57:59,000
If
There’s a ring, I assumed Binnaz aunt knew.

579
00:57:59,560 --> 00:58:01,520
Drop the act.

580
00:58:02,280 --> 00:58:07,240
Listen to me! If you interfere with
my relationship with Malik again,

581
00:58:07,600 --> 00:58:09,960
you’ll
see a very different Çiçek. Suit yourself.

582
00:58:10,520 --> 00:58:13,640
You won’t get away from me! You
understand?!

583
00:58:21,280 --> 00:58:24,320
And you’ll see a
very different Zehra, Miss. Çiçek.

584
00:59:00,680 --> 00:59:03,960
Short visits are best for the sick. Let’s
get going.

585
00:59:05,680 --> 00:59:08,320
We were just having a lovely conversation,
chatting.

586
00:59:09,120 --> 00:59:11,720
Short visits are best for the sick.
Come on, Yaşar.

587
00:59:12,960 --> 00:59:15,200
-Mrs. Mercan. Get well soon. -Thank you.

588
00:59:15,280 --> 00:59:16,720
Get well, Mr. Ateş.

589
00:59:16,880 --> 00:59:19,480
Demet, see you later.

590
00:59:19,560 --> 00:59:21,560
-See you later. -Thank you.

591
00:59:22,600 --> 00:59:24,040
See you, Mr. Nezir.

592
00:59:26,320 --> 00:59:27,760
Take care, Mr. Nezir.

593
00:59:32,960 --> 00:59:35,000
When
are you coming back to the company, Mercan?

594
00:59:35,440 --> 00:59:38,320
Also, it'll be a change for you.

595
00:59:42,080 --> 00:59:45,920
No rush. She needs rest.

596
00:59:49,360 --> 00:59:51,120
Yeah, I’m not ready yet.

597
00:59:59,080 --> 01:00:01,760
Rest, dear. Don't worry about work.

598
01:00:03,000 --> 01:00:04,760
Staying home isn’t good either.

599
01:00:05,080 --> 01:00:06,960
You should come. It’ll distract you.

600
01:00:16,440 --> 01:00:18,320
Any progress on the case?

601
01:00:19,160 --> 01:00:20,920
Did you find the men?

602
01:00:23,840 --> 01:00:25,320
We're investigating.

603
01:00:26,920 --> 01:00:28,640
So you haven’t found anything.

604
01:00:29,240 --> 01:00:32,280
I’m looking into it too,
but I haven’t found a lead yet.

605
01:00:35,080 --> 01:00:38,680
This isn’t the time
or the place to talk about this.

606
01:00:39,080 --> 01:00:40,720
It’s exactly the time and the place.

607
01:00:40,800 --> 01:00:42,240
The men are out there walking free.

608
01:00:42,320 --> 01:00:43,960
We've got to do something.

609
01:00:44,360 --> 01:00:46,200
They’ve probably run away by now.

610
01:00:48,480 --> 01:00:50,840
Maybe change the subject?

611
01:00:54,760 --> 01:00:56,680
I'd better go to my room.

612
01:00:57,800 --> 01:00:59,800
Are you okay?

613
01:01:03,160 --> 01:01:04,640
I’m fine.

614
01:01:06,840 --> 01:01:09,400
You don’t look fine. If there’s anything
I can...

615
01:01:09,840 --> 01:01:11,520
I know what she needs...

616
01:01:17,720 --> 01:01:19,400
rest.

617
01:01:23,560 --> 01:01:25,640
Come on, let's go upstairs to our room.

618
01:01:48,640 --> 01:01:51,680
Come, lie down a bit.
Take your medicine first.

619
01:02:00,160 --> 01:02:01,600
Thank you.

620
01:02:42,560 --> 01:02:43,920
I couldn't.

621
01:02:45,800 --> 01:02:48,720
I couldn’t stop that feeling of terror from
taking over.

622
01:02:50,840 --> 01:02:54,560
It feels like I’m back in the pool…

623
01:02:55,600 --> 01:02:57,680
…drowning again.

624
01:02:58,840 --> 01:03:01,720
I know I shouldn’t let it happen.

625
01:03:02,640 --> 01:03:05,440
I guess I'm not that strong.

626
01:03:27,000 --> 01:03:30,080
You're wrong. You're very strong.

627
01:03:32,920 --> 01:03:34,640
The incident is still fresh.

628
01:03:34,800 --> 01:03:36,320
It’s natural to feel this way.

629
01:03:40,200 --> 01:03:42,880
But to me, you're doing great.

630
01:03:44,920 --> 01:03:47,000
If it were anyone else in your place,

631
01:03:47,080 --> 01:03:48,760
they would’ve given up on life by now.

632
01:03:53,240 --> 01:03:54,560
I’m at fault too.

633
01:03:56,520 --> 01:03:57,840
I pushed you too much today.

634
01:03:59,440 --> 01:04:00,720
Come on, rest a little.

635
01:04:08,560 --> 01:04:11,560
- Speak, Cemal.
- Package delivered. We’re in the back.

636
01:04:12,400 --> 01:04:14,400
I’ll be right there.

637
01:04:15,680 --> 01:04:17,360
What happened? Where are you going?

638
01:04:19,320 --> 01:04:20,800
Work stuff. I’ll be right back.

639
01:04:21,640 --> 01:04:23,520
What did you talk about with Cemal?

640
01:04:24,400 --> 01:04:25,600
I said it's work stuff.

641
01:04:27,480 --> 01:04:29,240
Cemal found someone, didn’t he?

642
01:04:33,760 --> 01:04:36,800
Why are you stressing yourself and me with
these thoughts?

643
01:04:38,280 --> 01:04:40,040
There’s only one thing you need to do.

644
01:04:42,560 --> 01:04:44,360
And that's to take good care of yourself.

645
01:04:47,440 --> 01:04:51,040
You too. Please… be careful.

646
01:04:52,080 --> 01:04:53,880
I will.

647
01:05:01,280 --> 01:05:02,960
I’ll check your hands when you’re back.

648
01:05:03,760 --> 01:05:05,440
If you fought, I’ll know.

649
01:05:30,000 --> 01:05:31,480
I know you will.

650
01:05:33,000 --> 01:05:35,840
I’ll be here. Half an hour.

651
01:05:39,880 --> 01:05:41,760
Rest now. Okay?

652
01:05:42,680 --> 01:05:44,280
Don’t wear yourself out.

653
01:05:48,280 --> 01:05:50,120
I
Couldn’t bear even a single tear from you.

654
01:06:05,000 --> 01:06:06,320
Alright.

655
01:06:32,000 --> 01:06:33,720
Now your shift is starting. Watch it.

656
01:06:51,000 --> 01:06:53,400
Do you know the man with the tattoo on his
hand?

657
01:06:53,680 --> 01:06:56,920
I do… he’s my cousin. Kasım.

658
01:06:57,880 --> 01:07:00,720
I told your men already.
I swear I don’t know anything else.

659
01:07:01,640 --> 01:07:04,160
-Don't lie! -What’s going on?

660
01:07:05,000 --> 01:07:07,560
Supposedly he
knows one of the men who kidnapped Mercan.

661
01:07:08,640 --> 01:07:10,280
You must know something.

662
01:07:10,920 --> 01:07:12,480
I swear I don’t.

663
01:07:14,000 --> 01:07:16,080
He does shady stuff, I know that.

664
01:07:16,600 --> 01:07:18,320
We barely see each other.

665
01:07:18,760 --> 01:07:22,480
Look at that face. Lies all over it.

666
01:07:25,040 --> 01:07:27,840
Say the truth before I make you.

667
01:07:29,320 --> 01:07:31,320
When you get back, I’m checking your hands.

668
01:07:31,760 --> 01:07:33,760
If you fought, I’ll know.

669
01:07:42,440 --> 01:07:44,320
My lucky day!

670
01:07:50,200 --> 01:07:53,480
Listen. I’ll tell you a secret.

671
01:07:54,000 --> 01:07:55,400
See that man over there?

672
01:07:55,680 --> 01:07:58,240
The good‑looking one with
all the charisma. A real gentleman.

673
01:07:58,320 --> 01:07:59,720
He’s not actually a gentleman.

674
01:08:00,440 --> 01:08:02,160
He treats people the way they deserve.

675
01:08:02,280 --> 01:08:05,920
If you don’t tell the truth
in a minute, he’ll deal with you himself.

676
01:08:07,800 --> 01:08:10,480
He gave the job to me, but he’ll finish it
himself.

677
01:08:10,760 --> 01:08:14,040
Please, brother,
don’t! If I knew anything, I’d tell you!

678
01:08:14,480 --> 01:08:16,840
He said he doesn’t know. Just let him go.

679
01:08:25,360 --> 01:08:27,000
Please… let me go, brother.

680
01:08:29,320 --> 01:08:34,840
Cemal, it's obvious he’s not talking.

681
01:08:42,040 --> 01:08:43,640
Take him where he belongs.

682
01:08:48,920 --> 01:08:52,400
We did all we could, but you bought
your own ticket to the the graveyard.

683
01:08:52,680 --> 01:08:54,640
Pack up. You'll go on a journey.

684
01:08:54,880 --> 01:08:58,240
Wait! Don’t! I’ll talk!

685
01:09:06,800 --> 01:09:08,200
My cousin…

686
01:09:10,000 --> 01:09:11,640
told me about a job.

687
01:09:12,360 --> 01:09:15,520
He said someone came to him. Offered a lot
of money.

688
01:09:15,920 --> 01:09:17,440
Oh, really? Who's the man?

689
01:09:19,400 --> 01:09:21,040
I only know his name is Reşat.

690
01:09:22,120 --> 01:09:23,640
He didn’t say a last name.

691
01:09:24,920 --> 01:09:27,000
I swear that’s all.

692
01:09:27,720 --> 01:09:29,120
Where is your cousin now?

693
01:09:29,600 --> 01:09:32,480
I heard yesterday… he fled abroad.

694
01:09:46,320 --> 01:09:47,680
What do you think?

695
01:09:49,520 --> 01:09:51,960
Obviously, he knows nothing.

696
01:09:54,240 --> 01:09:55,800
But at least we have a name.

697
01:10:01,440 --> 01:10:05,920
He’s got a record. Are we letting him go?

698
01:10:06,920 --> 01:10:10,040
No. Hand him to the police.

699
01:10:10,400 --> 01:10:12,120
Share everything you know.

700
01:10:13,280 --> 01:10:14,640
We focus on this Reşat.

701
01:10:15,480 --> 01:10:16,920
Alright. On it.

702
01:10:18,320 --> 01:10:20,920
Come on,
we're going on a pleasant journey. Get up.

703
01:10:43,880 --> 01:10:45,280
Yes? Did you need something?

704
01:10:46,320 --> 01:10:49,240
I did. I know you’re putting on an act.

705
01:10:50,160 --> 01:10:52,320
You may fool Ateş, but not me.

706
01:10:53,320 --> 01:10:54,640
I’m warning you.

707
01:10:56,240 --> 01:10:58,840
He’s only helping you out of pity.

708
01:11:02,320 --> 01:11:04,880
Don’t fool yourself.
Ateş would never look at you.

709
01:11:06,720 --> 01:11:09,480
Are you done? I’d like to read.

710
01:11:10,440 --> 01:11:11,960
I’m not done!

711
01:11:12,320 --> 01:11:14,320
Enough lying in bed. Get up.

712
01:11:17,200 --> 01:11:18,920
Get up and be useful for once.

713
01:11:27,160 --> 01:11:28,720
Please leave my room.

714
01:11:30,120 --> 01:11:32,640
Your tongue’s gotten sharp.

715
01:11:32,800 --> 01:11:35,480
You’re hiding behind Ateş’s compassion.

716
01:11:36,080 --> 01:11:37,720
But I’m still here.

717
01:11:37,800 --> 01:11:41,760
I won’t let
you use my son’s conscience. Remember that.

718
01:11:53,680 --> 01:11:55,280
What’s going on?

719
01:11:55,720 --> 01:11:57,280
Nothing.

720
01:11:57,920 --> 01:12:00,120
I came to check on her.

721
01:12:00,360 --> 01:12:02,440
Her sulking has gone on long enough.

722
01:12:08,320 --> 01:12:11,440
I reminded her to pull herself together.

723
01:12:20,200 --> 01:12:22,000
Did she do something to you?

724
01:12:23,880 --> 01:12:26,920
No. She didn't.

725
01:12:28,040 --> 01:12:29,760
Your face says otherwise.

726
01:12:35,280 --> 01:12:36,840
Please don’t look at me like that.

727
01:12:38,560 --> 01:12:39,960
Like what?

728
01:12:41,720 --> 01:12:43,200
Like you pity me.

729
01:12:46,720 --> 01:12:49,240
I’ll take care of myself.

730
01:12:51,440 --> 01:12:53,360
I don’t want to be a burden.

731
01:12:56,240 --> 01:12:58,120
If you excuse me, I’m going to sleep now.

732
01:13:31,520 --> 01:13:32,720
What did you do to Mercan?

733
01:13:33,440 --> 01:13:36,520
What you should’ve done. I put her in her
place.

734
01:13:37,760 --> 01:13:40,760
Mother Müzeyyen, Leave Mercan alone.

735
01:13:41,560 --> 01:13:43,160
She’s been through enough.

736
01:13:45,040 --> 01:13:46,120
Excuse me son,

737
01:13:46,200 --> 01:13:49,800
but I’m not going
to worship Haydar’s daughter like you do.

738
01:13:49,880 --> 01:13:51,120
If she died, I wouldn’t care.

739
01:13:54,440 --> 01:13:55,920
What happened to your conscience?

740
01:14:01,120 --> 01:14:03,960
I buried it with my husband and my son.

741
01:14:04,800 --> 01:14:07,160
I left my heart by the graveyard, that day.

742
01:14:07,920 --> 01:14:10,920
All these years,
my heart has been beating there, not here.

743
01:14:15,360 --> 01:14:17,920
My heart turned
to stone the day Haydar took them from me.

744
01:14:18,440 --> 01:14:20,520
It won’t soften again, like yours.

745
01:14:22,240 --> 01:14:26,120
What I’m saying is, I have no mercy
left for the Yıldırıms.

746
01:14:27,080 --> 01:14:30,280
Mercan is my wife. Not a Yıldırım.

747
01:14:30,760 --> 01:14:32,120
She’s a Karahan.

748
01:14:32,520 --> 01:14:33,800
Sounds you forgot it?

749
01:14:37,480 --> 01:14:38,760
For now.

750
01:14:39,320 --> 01:14:41,240
You’re divorcing her. Did you forget?

751
01:14:43,560 --> 01:14:46,640
Mother Müzeyyen, I'm warning you
the last time.

752
01:14:47,480 --> 01:14:50,480
From now on, you
don’t enter that room when I’m not there.

753
01:14:50,560 --> 01:14:53,080
You don’t talk to her.

754
01:15:02,680 --> 01:15:07,080
If I see you hurt her again, you’ll answer
to me.

755
01:16:27,480 --> 01:16:29,320
What are you doing at the window?

756
01:16:29,480 --> 01:16:31,480
Sneaking around again?

757
01:16:31,560 --> 01:16:33,960
How
many times will I have to tell you, Çiçek?

758
01:16:34,600 --> 01:16:39,080
I can’t rip Malik out
of my heart just because you want me to.

759
01:16:39,440 --> 01:16:41,240
Then I’ll do it for you.

760
01:16:41,480 --> 01:16:45,640
Better one day of pain than a lifetime.

761
01:16:48,880 --> 01:16:52,680
You will not be with Malik.
Get that in your head.

762
01:16:53,960 --> 01:16:56,240
Mom, I love him!

763
01:16:59,720 --> 01:17:03,880
Even if my body isn’t with him,
my soul will be. How will you stop that?

764
01:17:06,640 --> 01:17:10,720
Rip my heart out? What do you want?

765
01:17:11,720 --> 01:17:13,240
What?

766
01:17:17,680 --> 01:17:19,200
You… you’re in love with Malik?!

767
01:17:48,280 --> 01:17:49,840
Hello.

768
01:17:50,440 --> 01:17:52,080
Finally, Ziya.

769
01:17:52,560 --> 01:17:55,040
You called a dozen times.

770
01:17:55,520 --> 01:17:57,280
I saw it but couldn’t get back to you.

771
01:17:57,440 --> 01:17:58,760
Hope you didn’t mind.

772
01:17:58,840 --> 01:18:01,160
Busy days.

773
01:18:01,480 --> 01:18:02,800
No problem.

774
01:18:03,080 --> 01:18:07,160
You built yourself a whole new circle. You
disappeared for years.

775
01:18:07,880 --> 01:18:11,840
What’s going on, Haydar? Tell me.

776
01:18:12,920 --> 01:18:14,480
You’re right to be upset.

777
01:18:14,840 --> 01:18:18,720
Life… work… you know how it is.

778
01:18:19,080 --> 01:18:21,280
Old friends don’t become enemies.

779
01:18:21,480 --> 01:18:24,120
We did a lot of work together.

780
01:18:24,480 --> 01:18:26,480
I made good money thanks to you.

781
01:18:27,280 --> 01:18:29,360
You know, my door is always open.

782
01:18:29,880 --> 01:18:33,280
I appreciate
it. Same goes for you. Don’t forget that.

783
01:18:33,600 --> 01:18:35,120
Well...

784
01:18:35,440 --> 01:18:39,280
If possible
I need to see you tomorrow. It’s important.

785
01:18:40,680 --> 01:18:42,960
Fine. I’ll send you the location.

786
01:18:44,000 --> 01:18:45,960
Good. Thanks. See you then.

787
01:18:50,560 --> 01:18:52,440
Your end is near, Ateş Karahan.

788
01:18:54,000 --> 01:18:57,960
I’ll find out exactly who you are.

789
01:19:30,560 --> 01:19:32,200
I’m warning you.

790
01:19:33,280 --> 01:19:36,120
He’s only helping you out of pity.

791
01:19:37,040 --> 01:19:39,640
Don’t fool yourself.
Ateş would never look at you.

792
01:19:40,760 --> 01:19:43,240
I won’t let you use my son’s conscience.

793
01:19:43,480 --> 01:19:44,840
Remember that.

794
01:19:56,240 --> 01:19:58,440
What’s wrong? Are you alright?

795
01:19:59,880 --> 01:20:01,160
I’m so cold.

796
01:20:56,080 --> 01:20:58,080
This isn’t right.

797
01:20:58,880 --> 01:21:00,400
The blanket didn't help much.

798
01:21:00,480 --> 01:21:01,920
Let's go to the doctor.

799
01:21:02,160 --> 01:21:03,840
No… I’ll warm up.

800
01:21:04,440 --> 01:21:07,000
Come on.
Don’t be stubborn. Let’s go to the doctor.

801
01:21:10,120 --> 01:21:13,840
It’ll pass.

802
01:21:16,920 --> 01:21:19,240
Sure it'll pass. You’ll be okay.

803
01:21:24,800 --> 01:21:28,160
Don’t let go. Please don’t go.

804
01:21:43,160 --> 01:21:44,360
I won’t.

805
01:21:44,640 --> 01:21:46,640
I'll be right by your
side until you recover.

806
01:21:51,160 --> 01:21:52,880
We’ll get through this together.

807
01:22:03,280 --> 01:22:05,480
I’ve become a burden to you.

808
01:22:06,080 --> 01:22:08,200
Hey…

809
01:22:08,480 --> 01:22:11,360
don’t say that. Ever.

810
01:22:13,080 --> 01:22:15,080
You’re not my burden, you’re my strength.

811
01:22:20,080 --> 01:22:21,360
Hear that?

812
01:22:26,520 --> 01:22:27,840
Come on.

813
01:22:37,320 --> 01:22:40,240
Close your eyes. I’m right here. Come on.

814
01:22:51,360 --> 01:22:53,120
I know this love is impossible…

815
01:22:54,560 --> 01:22:56,200
but I can’t fight it anymore.

816
01:22:57,840 --> 01:22:59,560
I lost that battle long ago.

817
01:23:01,280 --> 01:23:02,600
I'm defeated.

818
01:23:03,480 --> 01:23:07,680
Because
my heart loved you against every obstacle.

819
01:23:09,640 --> 01:23:14,160
A love so consuming there’s no room
left for anything else.

820
01:23:27,240 --> 01:23:29,360
You are my fierce, impossible love,

821
01:23:29,920 --> 01:23:35,040
my deepest ache, my sweetest wound.

822
01:23:36,800 --> 01:23:38,680
A wound I don’t want to heal,

823
01:23:39,880 --> 01:23:41,600
one I remember every time it bleeds.

824
01:23:53,840 --> 01:23:55,840
The half of me I can’t live without.

825
01:23:57,840 --> 01:23:59,400
You're my other half.

826
01:25:53,720 --> 01:25:56,440
Sorry… I mean, sorry
I fell asleep like that.

827
01:25:58,320 --> 01:25:59,440
I must’ve disturbed you.

828
01:25:59,520 --> 01:26:01,480
You probably couldn’t sleep because of me.

829
01:26:01,800 --> 01:26:04,160
It was the most peaceful sleep of my life.

830
01:26:05,480 --> 01:26:07,320
I could stay like this forever.

831
01:26:08,920 --> 01:26:10,480
What matters is that you rested.

832
01:26:13,080 --> 01:26:14,440
Thank you…

833
01:26:16,840 --> 01:26:18,720
You’ve been very kind to me lately.

834
01:26:22,480 --> 01:26:24,440
I mean… since we usually fight.

835
01:26:26,520 --> 01:26:27,960
Of course you pity me.

836
01:26:29,040 --> 01:26:30,680
What else could it be?

837
01:26:32,560 --> 01:26:33,720
Don’t get used to it.

838
01:26:34,880 --> 01:26:38,760
Once you’re better, we’ll
continue our fights from where we left off.

839
01:26:41,120 --> 01:26:43,880
Okay. Then… good morning.

840
01:26:45,360 --> 01:26:46,640
Good morning.

841
01:26:57,720 --> 01:27:00,040
-Yeah, Cemal? -Good news, bro.

842
01:27:00,120 --> 01:27:02,360
We found
the address of the man we were looking for.

843
01:27:06,040 --> 01:27:08,680
Great. Send it to me. I’m coming over now.

844
01:27:09,840 --> 01:27:12,120
-What happened? -Nothing.

845
01:27:12,840 --> 01:27:14,760
I can see something happened.

846
01:27:16,560 --> 01:27:19,240
We
Found the man connected to your situation.

847
01:27:20,600 --> 01:27:23,040
-I’m coming too. -No, you’re not.

848
01:27:23,640 --> 01:27:27,080
-But I... -You’re staying here and resting.

849
01:27:30,600 --> 01:27:31,800
Lie down.

850
01:27:37,880 --> 01:27:39,640
Don’t get out of bed.

851
01:27:57,280 --> 01:27:58,800
The company lawyer had objections

852
01:27:58,880 --> 01:28:01,920
to
The terms of the Cevizci Holding agreement.

853
01:28:02,000 --> 01:28:03,680
Inform the other side first,

854
01:28:03,760 --> 01:28:05,000
but before that,

855
01:28:05,080 --> 01:28:09,640
organize the safety meeting
so everyone can add it to their work plan.

856
01:28:09,800 --> 01:28:15,640
But actually, before
that, get the performance reports from HR…

857
01:28:16,000 --> 01:28:17,720
Okay, Miss Zahide…

858
01:28:18,400 --> 01:28:23,760
first the Cevizci Holding safety…

859
01:28:24,520 --> 01:28:27,760
then for the lawyers the
performance reports…

860
01:28:30,280 --> 01:28:33,240
and for HR… people…

861
01:28:33,480 --> 01:28:36,200
Someone like
you of course messes up like this.

862
01:28:36,360 --> 01:28:38,080
People mess up...

863
01:28:41,640 --> 01:28:43,960
No, no, actually that’s not what I meant to
say.

864
01:28:44,040 --> 01:28:47,760
I’m a
hundred percent with you I mean, with you.

865
01:28:48,480 --> 01:28:52,000
If this is your hundred
percent, things don’t look good, Mr. Yaşar.

866
01:28:52,560 --> 01:28:55,800
Um, Miss. Zahide,

867
01:28:56,240 --> 01:28:58,080
I didn’t do my morning yoga, that’s why.

868
01:28:58,160 --> 01:29:01,200
If I skip it, I can’t
pull myself together and get really cranky.

869
01:29:01,280 --> 01:29:06,400
I’ll do some mind yoga
soon. I’ll be sharp as a knife in an hour.

870
01:29:07,440 --> 01:29:11,040
Dear Mr. Yaşar, please
do your yoga before working hours.

871
01:29:11,120 --> 01:29:16,560
Whether you do yoga, somersaults,
or handstands is your business.

872
01:29:16,720 --> 01:29:17,920
But please be here.

873
01:29:18,080 --> 01:29:22,800
See? The lovebirds are laughing too.

874
01:29:23,120 --> 01:29:25,560
Miss. Zahide scolded me because I didn’t do
my yoga on time…

875
01:29:25,720 --> 01:29:28,520
Well, She really cares about my health.

876
01:29:29,880 --> 01:29:35,800
So… which concert are you two going to this
week?

877
01:29:39,280 --> 01:29:43,560
Concert? I don’t know…

878
01:29:44,640 --> 01:29:46,040
We’ll see…

879
01:29:46,120 --> 01:29:48,040
Go. Just go.

880
01:29:48,320 --> 01:29:51,800
You
found each other, just go. Go again, even.

881
01:29:52,160 --> 01:29:53,640
Nice. Really.

882
01:29:55,200 --> 01:29:58,560
People like me can rot at home alone.

883
01:29:58,960 --> 01:30:01,720
Guys, what is this?

884
01:30:01,880 --> 01:30:04,640
Could someone tell me what’s going on here?
Really?

885
01:30:04,720 --> 01:30:07,480
You’re talking about
concerts and lonely hearts!

886
01:30:09,880 --> 01:30:11,400
Please focus on work!

887
01:30:11,480 --> 01:30:13,200
Please come to yourselves. Unbelievable!

888
01:30:13,280 --> 01:30:17,880
Um... Miss Zahide. Miss Zahide. I said I'm
with you hundred percent...

889
01:30:18,200 --> 01:30:20,000
If I could just do my yoga for once...

890
01:30:25,720 --> 01:30:27,640
-Let's get back to work. -Demet...

891
01:30:28,760 --> 01:30:32,440
-Coffee on the break? -Yes.

892
01:30:32,880 --> 01:30:35,560
-Chocolate too? -Yes.

893
01:30:37,160 --> 01:30:39,200
-Let's work. -Let's work.

894
01:30:43,160 --> 01:30:44,560
A concert together,

895
01:30:46,200 --> 01:30:47,920
huh… with my sister.

896
01:31:35,840 --> 01:31:37,840
O Allah...,

897
01:31:41,760 --> 01:31:45,320
O Allah..., You are the
refuge of the helpless,

898
01:31:47,960 --> 01:31:50,800
the one the troubled turn to for relief.

899
01:31:52,920 --> 01:31:55,040
Nowhere else to go

900
01:31:56,280 --> 01:32:00,040
no one else to ask for help.

901
01:32:02,760 --> 01:32:05,400
Only You open Your arms to every servant.

902
01:32:07,080 --> 01:32:11,240
I loved a girl, O Allah.

903
01:32:14,000 --> 01:32:16,160
You
brought us together on the path of destiny,

904
01:32:17,360 --> 01:32:19,480
but people are trying to separate us.

905
01:32:20,160 --> 01:32:22,560
I have
fallen upon Your promise. Help me, O Allah.

906
01:32:23,360 --> 01:32:24,840
Help me, O Allah.

907
01:32:28,840 --> 01:32:33,720
Don’t
separate my heart from my Çiçek, O Allah…

908
01:32:35,120 --> 01:32:38,360
Let me reunite
with the one I love, return to my hometown,

909
01:32:40,680 --> 01:32:44,200
build our family, and live in peace.

910
01:32:46,840 --> 01:32:48,680
O Allah...

911
01:32:49,920 --> 01:32:55,040
protect the one I love and my love.

912
01:32:56,520 --> 01:33:01,960
You are the One who hears every
servant and accepts their prayers, O Allah.

913
01:33:22,240 --> 01:33:25,360
Look, gentlemen, this man is important
to Ateş and me.

914
01:33:25,720 --> 01:33:27,120
Don't let him escape.

915
01:33:27,400 --> 01:33:29,200
If you do let him slip away,

916
01:33:29,280 --> 01:33:31,760
you’ll be the ones running from
Ateş tonight.

917
01:33:48,600 --> 01:33:51,120
No
One uses a gun unless absolutely necessary.

918
01:33:53,880 --> 01:33:57,760
We’ll grab the man quietly
and make him talk the right way.

919
01:33:59,120 --> 01:34:02,720
Once we know who he works for, we hand them
all over to the police.

920
01:34:04,960 --> 01:34:06,560
Everyone, get in the cars. Come on.

921
01:34:43,200 --> 01:34:44,520
Slow down!!

922
01:34:48,680 --> 01:34:50,920
I was going to say… could you drive slower?

923
01:34:52,120 --> 01:34:54,360
Where
did you come from? What are you doing here?

924
01:34:58,640 --> 01:35:00,600
I didn’t want to stay alone at the mansion.

925
01:35:23,400 --> 01:35:26,440
And this is
my issue too. I need to be there.

926
01:35:26,720 --> 01:35:28,800
We don’t know what we’ll face there.

927
01:35:29,040 --> 01:35:31,880
A
Gun could go off. I can’t risk you, you...

928
01:35:33,080 --> 01:35:35,280
-You... -I feel safe with you.

929
01:35:38,440 --> 01:35:39,800
Please let me come.

930
01:35:42,440 --> 01:35:46,240
No. I’m taking you back.

931
01:35:47,320 --> 01:35:48,960
I’ll call Cemal.

932
01:35:51,040 --> 01:35:52,120
Oh God…

933
01:35:55,760 --> 01:35:57,560
You said you wouldn’t leave me.

934
01:35:57,920 --> 01:35:59,360
You said you’d protect me.

935
01:35:59,840 --> 01:36:02,200
-I
Did, but... -You changed your mind so fast.

936
01:36:05,560 --> 01:36:08,360
Please. Don’t leave
me alone. This is important to me.

937
01:36:11,040 --> 01:36:12,680
You’re important to me too!

938
01:36:19,320 --> 01:36:20,960
I mean…

939
01:36:21,360 --> 01:36:24,640
while you’re under my responsibility,
I can’t let anything happen to you.

940
01:36:27,120 --> 01:36:28,880
I can’t take the risk of going there.

941
01:36:32,840 --> 01:36:36,600
Look, I’ve shut myself inside for days.

942
01:36:37,400 --> 01:36:38,760
I’m scared, yes.

943
01:36:40,320 --> 01:36:41,600
But not with you.

944
01:36:45,440 --> 01:36:47,720
Because you won’t let
anything happen to me.

945
01:36:48,560 --> 01:36:49,720
I know that.

946
01:36:51,920 --> 01:36:55,400
I’m safer with you than anywhere else.

947
01:36:59,840 --> 01:37:04,640
And you told
me to face my fears. That’s what I’m doing.

948
01:37:10,240 --> 01:37:12,120
You’re not going to listen to me, are you…

949
01:37:14,040 --> 01:37:15,160
Fine. One condition.

950
01:37:16,160 --> 01:37:17,640
You’ll listen to me there.

951
01:37:18,240 --> 01:37:20,160
You won’t get out of the car. Got it?

952
01:37:22,120 --> 01:37:25,280
Okay. Then floor it!

953
01:37:30,680 --> 01:37:32,760
I mean… let’s go.

954
01:37:34,320 --> 01:37:35,920
What am I going to do with you…

955
01:37:55,200 --> 01:37:57,480
No… she’s alive.

956
01:38:08,680 --> 01:38:13,000
You didn’t come down, so I made you a plate
myself.

957
01:38:16,160 --> 01:38:18,200
Come on, eat something and perk up.

958
01:38:21,320 --> 01:38:24,760
I’m not in the mood to
be revived by tomatoes and cucumbers.

959
01:38:25,560 --> 01:38:27,280
Dear...

960
01:38:33,640 --> 01:38:35,240
Mother, I don’t want anything.

961
01:38:36,440 --> 01:38:39,280
Not food, not going out...

962
01:38:39,520 --> 01:38:41,000
nothing.

963
01:38:43,280 --> 01:38:47,120
The more I try to pull Ateş
away from that girl, the closer they get.

964
01:38:48,560 --> 01:38:50,480
And that man still hasn’t called.

965
01:38:58,200 --> 01:38:59,520
Listen to me my beautiful girl,

966
01:39:00,840 --> 01:39:02,880
When you go to war,

967
01:39:03,040 --> 01:39:05,480
you
can be struck from places you never expect.

968
01:39:06,000 --> 01:39:08,240
So what do we do? Sit and cry?

969
01:39:08,880 --> 01:39:10,880
Or pack up and leave?

970
01:39:12,520 --> 01:39:15,240
Only the helpless or the fearful do that.

971
01:39:17,720 --> 01:39:20,160
My daughter is neither.

972
01:39:20,840 --> 01:39:23,960
At least
she wasn't, the last time I looked at her.

973
01:39:26,560 --> 01:39:30,200
If
I knew where I went wrong, I’d act again.

974
01:39:30,880 --> 01:39:32,360
But I don’t know…

975
01:39:35,480 --> 01:39:37,800
You’re trying to take the shortcut.

976
01:39:38,520 --> 01:39:41,000
But some victories take the long road.

977
01:39:42,360 --> 01:39:46,840
You must do not what comes to mind
first, but what never comes to mind.

978
01:39:48,600 --> 01:39:49,640
Meaning?

979
01:39:52,440 --> 01:39:55,160
The important thing isn’t Mercan dying.

980
01:39:55,800 --> 01:39:58,320
It’s Mercan dying in Ateş’s heart.

981
01:40:01,160 --> 01:40:03,920
Okay, but how do we… I mean, how do we get
her out of Ateş’s...

982
01:40:05,320 --> 01:40:07,040
…mind.

983
01:40:08,840 --> 01:40:13,720
We must do something
that makes Ateş unable to even look at her.

984
01:40:14,840 --> 01:40:18,120
Not a trace of Mercan should remain in his
mind or his heart.

985
01:40:18,800 --> 01:40:20,640
Right?

986
01:40:53,400 --> 01:40:55,000
-Stay in the car. -Okay.

987
01:40:55,480 --> 01:40:56,760
I won’t get out of the car.

988
01:40:57,880 --> 01:40:59,440
Okay.

989
01:41:02,760 --> 01:41:05,360
Be
Careful. Don’t let anything happen to you.

990
01:41:19,200 --> 01:41:21,520
God,
please don’t let anything happen to them.

991
01:42:41,400 --> 01:42:42,720
He’s running!

992
01:42:43,280 --> 01:42:45,960
-Catch him! -Get him!

993
01:42:59,200 --> 01:43:00,680
Stay with Mercan. We’ll handle it.

994
01:43:21,640 --> 01:43:22,880
I was so scared…

995
01:43:54,800 --> 01:43:56,880
Don’t be scared. I’m here.

996
01:43:58,000 --> 01:43:59,680
Nothing will happen to you.

997
01:44:12,920 --> 01:44:14,960
Seeing you like this hurts me.

998
01:44:28,440 --> 01:44:30,040
They’ll catch him…

999
01:44:50,480 --> 01:44:51,840
My beautiful Çiçek.

1000
01:44:54,920 --> 01:44:56,920
My love who makes everything beautiful…

1001
01:45:03,680 --> 01:45:05,120
Malik!

1002
01:45:11,280 --> 01:45:12,560
What is this, man!

1003
01:45:13,760 --> 01:45:15,320
What is this? Huh?

1004
01:45:15,800 --> 01:45:19,520
How can
a man set his eyes on his friend’s sister?

1005
01:45:19,760 --> 01:45:22,560
Berat, it’s not like that. I didn’t "set
my eyes" on anyone.

1006
01:45:22,920 --> 01:45:24,840
Calm down. Sit, let’s talk.

1007
01:45:26,120 --> 01:45:28,560
Malik, what kind of a person are you?

1008
01:45:29,120 --> 01:45:30,280
What kind of a person?

1009
01:45:30,960 --> 01:45:32,800
We opened our table to you.

1010
01:45:33,240 --> 01:45:34,440
And what did you do?

1011
01:45:34,520 --> 01:45:36,800
Man, you betrayed us.

1012
01:45:37,440 --> 01:45:40,640
Huh? Were you laughing behind my back?

1013
01:45:40,760 --> 01:45:44,080
Having fun while I trusted you? Huh?

1014
01:45:45,040 --> 01:45:49,080
Berat, I love Çiçek... my intention is not
bad.

1015
01:45:49,440 --> 01:45:53,600
Don’t start with your intentions! Malik!

1016
01:45:53,960 --> 01:45:55,600
From now on,

1017
01:45:55,840 --> 01:45:57,440
You’ll stop seeing Çiçek

1018
01:45:57,800 --> 01:46:00,360
or I won’t hold back. You got it?

1019
01:46:00,440 --> 01:46:02,120
-Malik! -Brother!

1020
01:46:02,200 --> 01:46:04,680
-Aah! -Calm down! What are you doing!

1021
01:46:10,960 --> 01:46:12,600
We don’t have bad intentions!

1022
01:46:12,680 --> 01:46:14,720
We only love each other.

1023
01:46:19,600 --> 01:46:22,520
Be
Quiet, Çiçek! Don’t make me lose control!

1024
01:46:28,880 --> 01:46:31,520
Man, I’ll
settle my debt to you as soon as possible.

1025
01:46:31,840 --> 01:46:33,160
Got it, Malik?

1026
01:46:33,240 --> 01:46:36,240
After
that, I don’t care if you’re dead or alive.

1027
01:46:36,840 --> 01:46:39,640
-Çiçek, move! -Berat! Berat, listen!

1028
01:46:41,960 --> 01:46:43,560
-Çiçek, move!

1029
01:46:44,400 --> 01:46:45,760
Brother...

1030
01:46:53,520 --> 01:46:56,000
-Brother... -Çiçek, I told you to move.

1031
01:46:57,160 --> 01:46:58,640
Move!

1032
01:47:45,120 --> 01:47:48,320
-Talk to me, Cemal. -He got away.

1033
01:47:54,160 --> 01:47:58,000
Okay. Just in case, leave
one of the guys here.

1034
01:47:59,480 --> 01:48:00,840
Okay.

1035
01:48:02,480 --> 01:48:05,200
-What happened? -The man escaped.

1036
01:48:07,840 --> 01:48:10,520
If you hadn’t
insisted on coming, we would’ve caught him.

1037
01:48:11,840 --> 01:48:16,160
Or while you
were chasing him, you could’ve gotten hurt…

1038
01:48:16,360 --> 01:48:17,640
or God forbid...

1039
01:48:19,720 --> 01:48:24,760
Hey, okay... okay…

1040
01:48:26,680 --> 01:48:27,920
Don’t worry.

1041
01:48:35,480 --> 01:48:37,320
If we found him once, we’ll find him again.

1042
01:48:38,200 --> 01:48:41,360
If not today, then tomorrow. If not
tomorrow, the next day.

1043
01:48:49,080 --> 01:48:53,480
A man I want to catch has nowhere to run.

1044
01:49:01,360 --> 01:49:03,880
Let's go now.

1045
01:50:28,320 --> 01:50:33,720
Let me make the coffee...

1046
01:50:37,520 --> 01:50:40,560
Hey! Hold it right there.

1047
01:50:40,840 --> 01:50:43,520
Huh? Having fun?

1048
01:50:43,600 --> 01:50:45,880
-Concerts and all that? -Nezir Bey...

1049
01:50:46,240 --> 01:50:47,640
Fun’s over.

1050
01:50:48,000 --> 01:50:50,520
If I see you around my sister again,

1051
01:50:50,680 --> 01:50:54,280
I won’t
just get you fired. I’ll break your bones.

1052
01:50:56,320 --> 01:50:59,400
In that case you won’t be able to go to the
bathroom, forget concerts.

1053
01:50:59,680 --> 01:51:01,520
-Mr. Nezir... -Shut up, man!

1054
01:51:02,560 --> 01:51:04,960
Who do you think you are, huh? You, son of
a...

1055
01:51:05,880 --> 01:51:06,880
-Huh? -Mr. Nezir...

1056
01:51:06,960 --> 01:51:11,040
Shut up, man. You
think you’re on Demet’s level, you mutt?

1057
01:51:11,480 --> 01:51:14,200
She’s the sister of Nezir Keseroğlu.

1058
01:51:14,440 --> 01:51:16,880
And you… you’re a cheap intern.

1059
01:51:20,320 --> 01:51:23,760
I’m telling you
for the last time. Know your place.

1060
01:51:24,520 --> 01:51:27,600
Okay? You’re young. Don’t ruin your life.

1061
01:51:27,720 --> 01:51:29,080
Mr. Nezir...

1062
01:51:40,840 --> 01:51:43,400
I'll break that glass on your head!

1063
01:51:55,520 --> 01:51:59,520
One day you’ll learn who I really
am. And then I’ll make you answer for this.

1064
01:52:00,240 --> 01:52:02,280
Then we’ll see what you do.

1065
01:52:13,560 --> 01:52:16,040
One day everyone will learn who’s who.

1066
01:53:05,800 --> 01:53:08,560
May your beautiful face always be
touched by happiness.

1067
01:53:22,000 --> 01:53:23,440
ANLAŞILMADI

1068
01:53:24,400 --> 01:53:25,560
-Enjoy it. -Thank you.

1069
01:53:25,640 --> 01:53:27,920
-Thank you. -Here.

1070
01:53:30,880 --> 01:53:31,880
Thank you.

1071
01:53:31,960 --> 01:53:35,640
- Thank you.
- Thank you, sir. May God bless you.

1072
01:53:43,200 --> 01:53:45,680
It’s so beautiful. I’m glad we came.

1073
01:53:46,680 --> 01:53:50,200
Of course you’re glad, stowaway.

1074
01:53:51,600 --> 01:53:54,800
Admit it. You’re glad
I came. You’d be bored without me.

1075
01:53:56,320 --> 01:53:58,120
If that’s what you want to believe, fine.

1076
01:54:03,280 --> 01:54:04,720
It’s really good.

1077
01:54:19,400 --> 01:54:20,600
Are you cold?

1078
01:54:23,640 --> 01:54:25,360
Oh, no, thanks, I’m fine.

1079
01:54:26,320 --> 01:54:29,360
You’re cold. Don’t argue. It’s chilly.

1080
01:54:59,080 --> 01:55:00,720
But then you’ll be cold.

1081
01:55:01,760 --> 01:55:04,520
Nothing will happen to
me. Don’t worry about me.

1082
01:55:12,520 --> 01:55:14,320
This place is so peaceful.

1083
01:55:15,400 --> 01:55:17,040
I feel calm… It's so beautiful.

1084
01:55:18,800 --> 01:55:19,800
Yeah.

1085
01:55:21,320 --> 01:55:22,920
I come here often.

1086
01:55:24,560 --> 01:55:26,600
So it’s not special for me, you always come
here?

1087
01:55:30,440 --> 01:55:31,800
Fine then.

1088
01:55:33,000 --> 01:55:36,800
When I leave, your troubles will
disappear and you’ll come here even more.

1089
01:55:39,360 --> 01:55:40,520
Where are you going?

1090
01:55:41,760 --> 01:55:43,520
Aren’t I going to London?

1091
01:55:46,320 --> 01:55:47,600
That plane is gone.

1092
01:55:52,640 --> 01:55:54,160
Aren't there other planes?

1093
01:55:57,840 --> 01:56:00,040
There’s no
plane that’s taking you far away anymore.

1094
01:56:09,880 --> 01:56:11,160
I mean…

1095
01:56:12,840 --> 01:56:16,400
well... um...

1096
01:56:17,280 --> 01:56:20,040
later you
can go on vacation or whatever, of course.

1097
01:56:20,840 --> 01:56:23,200
I’m just
saying because things are messy right now.

1098
01:56:24,320 --> 01:56:26,280
Oh, that’s why you’re saying it?

1099
01:56:31,160 --> 01:56:32,520
Okay then, I’ll do that.

1100
01:56:32,840 --> 01:56:37,160
I’ll
go on vacation later. Somewhere down south…

1101
01:56:41,600 --> 01:56:43,120
You’re getting spoiled again.

1102
01:56:44,680 --> 01:56:46,440
Clearly you’ve recovered.

1103
01:56:54,040 --> 01:56:55,400
But I was drinking that.

1104
01:56:55,640 --> 01:56:58,640
You can drink at
home. Come on, get in. I’ve got work to do.

1105
01:57:36,680 --> 01:57:41,000
Get inside, girl! Don't drive me crazy!

1106
01:57:41,920 --> 01:57:44,440
Are you trying to get
me into trouble, girl!?

1107
01:57:44,520 --> 01:57:46,920
What’s all this noise!? Did the world just
end?!

1108
01:57:47,000 --> 01:57:48,440
Brother, for God's sake...

1109
01:57:48,520 --> 01:57:51,280
Shut up. Look at your daughter!

1110
01:57:51,560 --> 01:57:53,400
Did you hear what she’s been doing?

1111
01:57:53,960 --> 01:57:55,720
Flirting around with Malik!

1112
01:57:55,800 --> 01:57:57,920
Brother, why are you this angry?

1113
01:57:58,160 --> 01:58:01,840
We didn’t do
anything wrong! We really love each other.

1114
01:58:02,560 --> 01:58:04,480
-Çiçek... -Mother...

1115
01:58:05,720 --> 01:58:08,720
You knew?

1116
01:58:09,160 --> 01:58:11,360
I knew, yes, but I didn’t tell you.

1117
01:58:11,520 --> 01:58:13,240
I handled it before it reached you.

1118
01:58:13,320 --> 01:58:15,440
Don’t worry. They won't see each other.

1119
01:58:15,520 --> 01:58:17,480
Mom, don’t... please, I’m begging you.

1120
01:58:17,560 --> 01:58:19,880
-Çiçek! -Don't do what?! What?!

1121
01:58:20,360 --> 01:58:22,280
Good for you! Good for
you my dearest mother.

1122
01:58:22,360 --> 01:58:25,200
All this was happening right under my nose
and I had no idea.

1123
01:58:27,760 --> 01:58:30,120
Listen to me, Çiçek. Listen! Çiçek!

1124
01:58:30,520 --> 01:58:32,600
Don’t push me into doing something worse.

1125
01:58:34,320 --> 01:58:37,200
I swear I’ll lock you in your room and you
won’t see daylight.

1126
01:58:37,520 --> 01:58:39,080
-Got it?! -Brother...

1127
01:58:39,480 --> 01:58:42,480
for God’s sake, why are you so angry?

1128
01:58:45,680 --> 01:58:49,720
Just because our father
isn’t here doesn’t mean you’re ownerless!

1129
01:58:49,960 --> 01:58:51,880
I’m the man of this house! I am!

1130
01:58:52,360 --> 01:58:54,000
You’re not without protection!

1131
01:58:54,520 --> 01:58:55,880
Do you understand, Çiçek?!

1132
01:58:57,080 --> 01:59:00,160
He'll watch his step. He’ll stay
away. Won't get closer than even a meter.

1133
01:59:00,600 --> 01:59:03,840
Got it? Period! Exclamation point!

1134
01:59:13,240 --> 01:59:14,280
Ahh, Çiçek, ahh.

1135
01:59:14,360 --> 01:59:17,520
Mother… At least you don’t do this. Please…

1136
01:59:17,600 --> 01:59:20,920
At least you
understand me… Is loving someone a crime!?

1137
01:59:21,120 --> 01:59:22,200
It is a crime.

1138
01:59:22,280 --> 01:59:25,040
If you love
the wrong man, that’s even a bigger crime.

1139
01:59:25,120 --> 01:59:27,200
I told you so that he shouldn't find out.

1140
01:59:27,640 --> 01:59:29,560
Don’t drag my son into trouble,

1141
01:59:29,640 --> 01:59:32,480
don’t destroy the peace of this
house. Enough, already.

1142
01:59:58,280 --> 01:59:59,600
What’s the latest?

1143
02:00:01,040 --> 02:00:02,760
I sent the men out.

1144
02:00:03,160 --> 02:00:06,560
They’re all out there searching
for the ones who kidnapped Mercan.

1145
02:00:08,200 --> 02:00:09,800
I’m not talking about that.

1146
02:00:10,280 --> 02:00:11,720
What did you do about the money?

1147
02:00:12,240 --> 02:00:14,920
I managed to get
into Keseroğlu Holding one way or another.

1148
02:00:15,320 --> 02:00:17,800
I’ll slowly expand my ground there.

1149
02:00:21,560 --> 02:00:23,560
These things can’t be rushed, Nermin.

1150
02:00:24,440 --> 02:00:28,400
The only thing we need to hurry about
is Ateş.

1151
02:00:29,520 --> 02:00:31,400
Don’t drag out the money issue either…

1152
02:00:32,560 --> 02:00:36,080
Look, the foundation elections are close.

1153
02:00:36,880 --> 02:00:39,720
I can’t let Müzeyyen take that seat.

1154
02:00:41,880 --> 02:00:44,840
Look what I’m dealing
with, and look what you’re worried about.

1155
02:00:45,480 --> 02:00:47,480
We’re worried about the same thing, Haydar.

1156
02:00:47,960 --> 02:00:52,000
If I win
the elections, Müzeyyen will lose her mind.

1157
02:00:54,200 --> 02:00:55,960
And so?

1158
02:00:57,480 --> 02:00:59,960
So that’s a kind of victory too.

1159
02:01:04,840 --> 02:01:06,480
For God's sake, Nermin.

1160
02:01:08,960 --> 02:01:10,360
Turn off the light.

1161
02:01:11,120 --> 02:01:13,000
Come on. Turn it off. Let's get to sleep.

1162
02:01:13,200 --> 02:01:14,360
Here, take this.

1163
02:01:16,400 --> 02:01:19,040
I
Want my power back, what’s wrong with that?

1164
02:01:20,280 --> 02:01:22,960
I was in the
foundation long before she ever showed up.

1165
02:01:28,800 --> 02:01:32,600
If anyone should be president, it’s me for
sure…

1166
02:01:34,280 --> 02:01:36,640
Yeah, she’ll be president and save us all…

1167
02:01:37,320 --> 02:01:38,520
Oh, God.

1168
02:01:55,280 --> 02:01:57,120
Can you turn the light back on?

1169
02:01:59,880 --> 02:02:01,760
You’ve read enough. Rest now.

1170
02:02:04,840 --> 02:02:06,200
No, it’s not that…

1171
02:02:10,440 --> 02:02:12,400
I don’t want to stay in the dark.

1172
02:02:16,240 --> 02:02:18,000
I'm sorry… I didn’t think of that.

1173
02:02:44,760 --> 02:02:45,920
Are you okay?

1174
02:02:53,920 --> 02:02:55,120
I don’t think so.

1175
02:03:03,520 --> 02:03:05,960
If I fall asleep…

1176
02:03:07,320 --> 02:03:10,400
I don’t want to have nightmares.

1177
02:03:11,760 --> 02:03:14,760
If I said let’s go rough
someone up, you’d follow me out the door.

1178
02:03:18,120 --> 02:03:22,120
I thought I could get over it.

1179
02:03:29,360 --> 02:03:30,920
I keep having nightmares.

1180
02:03:32,120 --> 02:03:35,880
The same moment over and over.

1181
02:03:36,600 --> 02:03:41,040
People rest when they sleep, but I suffer.

1182
02:03:41,600 --> 02:03:44,880
The water rising...

1183
02:03:51,600 --> 02:03:52,680
It’ll pass…

1184
02:03:58,640 --> 02:04:00,600
We talked about this. With time.

1185
02:04:06,080 --> 02:04:08,920
How much time? A lot?

1186
02:04:14,160 --> 02:04:15,480
Let’s hope it’s short.

1187
02:04:19,040 --> 02:04:22,440
But however long it takes, I’ll be here.

1188
02:04:36,560 --> 02:04:39,800
I’m so glad you’re here with me.

1189
02:04:46,600 --> 02:04:50,200
Come on,
let’s go out to the balcony. Get some air.

1190
02:04:51,720 --> 02:04:55,240
You mean change the atmosphere. Fine.

1191
02:05:28,560 --> 02:05:29,880
Come here.

1192
02:05:33,160 --> 02:05:34,280
Let me help you.

1193
02:06:09,920 --> 02:06:11,280
Man, look at Malik.

1194
02:06:12,400 --> 02:06:14,160
How can he do such a thing, man?

1195
02:06:18,680 --> 02:06:19,920
Unbelievable…

1196
02:06:24,800 --> 02:06:26,480
Alright, calm down, Berat.

1197
02:06:27,640 --> 02:06:30,360
Okay, they went behind your back.

1198
02:06:31,440 --> 02:06:34,960
Yes, it was
disrespectful. That’s exactly what it was…

1199
02:06:35,800 --> 02:06:38,280
But don’t
get yourself into trouble because of them.

1200
02:06:38,800 --> 02:06:42,360
So we can’t trust anyone now!?

1201
02:06:43,040 --> 02:06:44,080
Can we?

1202
02:06:46,360 --> 02:06:48,040
If my own sister does this!?

1203
02:06:51,160 --> 02:06:55,560
Though honestly, the real fault is Malik’s.

1204
02:06:56,560 --> 02:06:58,600
He got into her head. Can you believe it?

1205
02:07:00,760 --> 02:07:02,920
Walking around like he’s our friend…

1206
02:07:07,720 --> 02:07:11,120
Watch me. Watch me take care of him.

1207
02:07:11,800 --> 02:07:13,520
There's no Malik, any more.

1208
02:07:14,520 --> 02:07:17,480
He's done. He won’t even
be able to say hello to Çiçek again.

1209
02:07:19,040 --> 02:07:21,560
Look, my friendship is solid,

1210
02:07:22,080 --> 02:07:25,600
okay, but my enmity is worse…

1211
02:07:27,680 --> 02:07:29,680
Alright Berat, but...

1212
02:07:30,320 --> 02:07:33,800
what if they go
and get married behind your back?

1213
02:07:34,360 --> 02:07:36,600
You see, they’ve already gone wild.

1214
02:07:36,680 --> 02:07:38,120
You can expect anything from them.

1215
02:07:39,240 --> 02:07:40,720
Look, if that happens...

1216
02:07:41,800 --> 02:07:43,520
If that happens,

1217
02:07:43,720 --> 02:07:47,000
I won’t call Çiçek my
sister ever again. I’ll erase her for life.

1218
02:07:47,320 --> 02:07:48,880
Oh!

1219
02:07:52,880 --> 02:07:55,360
Sorry, Zehra. I got angry all of
a sudden...

1220
02:07:55,680 --> 02:07:57,360
I exploded. I'm so sorry.

1221
02:07:57,440 --> 02:07:59,440
-Okay. Okay. -Let me...

1222
02:08:01,840 --> 02:08:03,600
Okay, it’s fine.

1223
02:08:14,560 --> 02:08:17,400
I mean... in a situation like this,

1224
02:08:17,480 --> 02:08:20,160
we’re not
going to worry about spilled coffee. Right?

1225
02:08:20,840 --> 02:08:25,360
After all, your sister lied to your face,

1226
02:08:26,600 --> 02:08:31,080
and the man you called a friend stabbed you
in the back…

1227
02:08:32,120 --> 02:08:35,960
It's not that important. I’ll make a fresh
one. Okay?

1228
02:08:38,480 --> 02:08:40,560
Um... sorry about the trouble…

1229
02:08:41,040 --> 02:08:42,520
Please, Berat.

1230
02:08:44,360 --> 02:08:45,800
As long as you calm down.

1231
02:09:01,560 --> 02:09:04,800
You’ll get cold too. Here.

1232
02:09:22,960 --> 02:09:24,480
Endless, isn’t it?

1233
02:09:25,320 --> 02:09:26,720
So many stars.

1234
02:09:28,280 --> 02:09:32,800
Yeah. Look — that’s Orion…

1235
02:09:33,080 --> 02:09:36,160
that’s the Little Dipper, and that one’s
the Big Dipper.

1236
02:09:37,680 --> 02:09:39,800
Which ones? I didn't get it.

1237
02:09:40,840 --> 02:09:42,120
Like this…

1238
02:09:49,280 --> 02:09:53,400
Orion is one of the most recognizable
constellations in our hemisphere.

1239
02:09:57,080 --> 02:09:58,800
I always mix them up.

1240
02:09:59,760 --> 02:10:01,600
I don’t know as much as you.

1241
02:10:04,880 --> 02:10:07,200
Sometimes people make
the world feel too small for you.

1242
02:10:08,200 --> 02:10:10,400
That’s when you find comfort in the sky.

1243
02:10:13,160 --> 02:10:15,960
No one can stop you from
dreaming when you’re looking at the stars.

1244
02:10:18,960 --> 02:10:22,200
Dreaming is
for childhood. That’s long gone.

1245
02:10:26,200 --> 02:10:28,120
Dreams change as we grow.

1246
02:10:31,040 --> 02:10:34,560
So much ambition, so much cruelty…

1247
02:10:37,960 --> 02:10:40,520
We think we’re so big.

1248
02:10:41,440 --> 02:10:44,200
But in this huge universe, we’re tiny.

1249
02:10:51,920 --> 02:10:53,800
You’re not cold, right?

1250
02:10:54,000 --> 02:10:57,280
No. I’m very comfortable.

1251
02:10:57,920 --> 02:11:00,680
The air is nice. So clean.

1252
02:11:02,200 --> 02:11:05,680
I call nights like this "the most beautiful
of all."

1253
02:11:06,760 --> 02:11:08,040
When the sky is clear…

1254
02:11:09,080 --> 02:11:14,320
like black fabric stitched with sparkles.

1255
02:11:17,960 --> 02:11:19,720
Makes you feel alive.

1256
02:11:22,080 --> 02:11:23,600
Are you cold?

1257
02:11:24,840 --> 02:11:26,240
Impossible.

1258
02:11:27,280 --> 02:11:30,440
Your name is Ateş… must be because of that.

1259
02:11:34,800 --> 02:11:36,640
I really made that terrible joke, didn’t I?

1260
02:11:36,720 --> 02:11:38,440
You did.

1261
02:11:38,960 --> 02:11:40,080
Let’s forget it.

1262
02:11:40,560 --> 02:11:42,640
-Already did.-Great.

1263
02:11:44,560 --> 02:11:46,360
It’s so beautiful.

1264
02:11:47,640 --> 02:11:50,320
The more
you look, the more it pulls you in, right?

1265
02:11:54,600 --> 02:11:56,040
Yeah.

1266
02:11:57,560 --> 02:11:59,400
The more you look, the more you get lost.

1267
02:12:07,760 --> 02:12:10,520
You don’t want to be found again. You just
want to stay there.

1268
02:12:19,040 --> 02:12:21,640
All the stars have filled the night.

1269
02:12:24,600 --> 02:12:27,000
Yeah. There are a lot.

1270
02:12:34,200 --> 02:12:40,000
But my moon,
my star, my whole world is right beside me.

1271
02:12:41,040 --> 02:12:42,640
She’s filled my heart.

1272
02:12:44,720 --> 02:12:45,800
That’s where she lives.

1273
02:12:57,480 --> 02:12:58,720
Are you cold?

1274
02:14:44,640 --> 02:14:49,360
Come on,
go sleep in your bed. It’s cold out here.

1275
02:14:58,280 --> 02:15:01,240
Come on, you'll be cold here.

1276
02:15:02,920 --> 02:15:05,560
-Go lie in your bed. -No.

1277
02:15:06,680 --> 02:15:08,040
Can you be quiet?

1278
02:15:11,120 --> 02:15:12,400
Come on.

1279
02:15:14,280 --> 02:15:16,680
If you go to your bed, I’ll be quiet.

1280
02:15:18,440 --> 02:15:20,280
I’m fine like this. Please.

1281
02:15:22,480 --> 02:15:26,920
Come on… shh… you’ll get cold…

1282
02:15:29,840 --> 02:15:32,520
Come on… shh… get up...

1283
02:15:34,960 --> 02:15:37,840
-Good morning. -Good morning.

1284
02:15:43,360 --> 02:15:46,040
You didn’t let me sleep. I was sleeping so
well.

1285
02:15:53,560 --> 02:15:55,000
It's already morning.

1286
02:16:05,480 --> 02:16:09,520
How did I fall asleep like this?

1287
02:16:10,040 --> 02:16:12,120
Talking about stars and all…

1288
02:16:17,360 --> 02:16:19,120
Anyway...

1289
02:16:25,600 --> 02:16:27,480
I’m fine! I’m fine, it’s nothing!

1290
02:16:31,520 --> 02:16:32,880
Clumsy.

1291
02:16:47,760 --> 02:16:48,960
Ziya?

1292
02:16:49,120 --> 02:16:52,360
Looks like fate wanted
us to meet again before dying, Big Haydar.

1293
02:16:53,320 --> 02:16:56,200
We’ll be seeing each
other a lot more from now on, brother Ziya.

1294
02:16:56,440 --> 02:16:59,240
If you came to me, you’ve got trouble.

1295
02:16:59,320 --> 02:17:02,120
A man who doesn’t speak his trouble can’t
find a cure.

1296
02:17:02,800 --> 02:17:04,920
Tell me who upset you?

1297
02:17:12,560 --> 02:17:13,920
These ones…

1298
02:17:19,160 --> 02:17:22,320
No matter what I did,
I couldn’t find anything useful on them.

1299
02:17:23,320 --> 02:17:26,240
You’re a good mole. There’s no place you
haven’t slipped into.

1300
02:17:26,880 --> 02:17:28,480
Ask around.

1301
02:17:29,080 --> 02:17:31,440
Bring me whatever you can find about them.

1302
02:17:34,200 --> 02:17:36,160
Who are they? What are they?

1303
02:17:37,280 --> 02:17:39,320
That’s
exactly what I’m trying to find out, Ziya.

1304
02:17:40,680 --> 02:17:41,800
Exactly that.

1305
02:17:43,360 --> 02:17:45,240
This one is the head of the snake.

1306
02:17:45,320 --> 02:17:49,320
Ateş Karahan. The others
are just crumbs that’ll lead us to him.

1307
02:17:50,440 --> 02:17:52,800
I want to know everything you find.

1308
02:17:53,720 --> 02:17:55,960
Big or small. Everything.

1309
02:17:56,880 --> 02:17:58,160
Consider it done.

1310
02:18:01,360 --> 02:18:05,080
Bring me something useful, and I’ll set you
up for life.

1311
02:18:06,560 --> 02:18:08,160
I’ll pay you back many times over.

1312
02:18:08,240 --> 02:18:10,840
I don’t doubt it. This will be a good deal.

1313
02:18:11,880 --> 02:18:15,960
I’ll lay
out their whole past in front of you soon.

1314
02:18:16,400 --> 02:18:17,800
Don’t worry.

1315
02:18:19,480 --> 02:18:20,840
Thank you.

1316
02:18:33,680 --> 02:18:35,160
Are you still not done?

1317
02:18:37,440 --> 02:18:38,840
Not done.

1318
02:18:39,080 --> 02:18:41,000
What is it? I’m shaving.

1319
02:18:42,840 --> 02:18:44,160
You’re taking forever.

1320
02:18:45,000 --> 02:18:46,280
How much longer?

1321
02:18:47,240 --> 02:18:49,920
Five minutes. What is it?

1322
02:18:50,760 --> 02:18:53,600
I think my makeup is in there. I can’t find
it.

1323
02:18:55,400 --> 02:18:56,760
Wait a bit longer.

1324
02:18:57,760 --> 02:18:59,440
You can survive without makeup.

1325
02:19:01,720 --> 02:19:03,040
Ugh.

1326
02:19:03,440 --> 02:19:04,800
I heard that.

1327
02:19:07,280 --> 02:19:08,440
Ugh!

1328
02:19:10,760 --> 02:19:12,360
Come in if you want.

1329
02:19:15,800 --> 02:19:17,040
I’m coming.

1330
02:19:18,040 --> 02:19:19,200
Come in.

1331
02:19:26,720 --> 02:19:28,240
Come in.

1332
02:19:34,200 --> 02:19:36,200
Once you go in, you never come out.

1333
02:19:38,600 --> 02:19:40,280
Maybe you’re confusing me with yourself.

1334
02:19:40,680 --> 02:19:42,040
Absolutely not.

1335
02:19:43,000 --> 02:19:45,000
Ohm. Sure.

1336
02:19:45,160 --> 02:19:48,040
I didn’t keep
track of all the days I waited at the door.

1337
02:19:50,240 --> 02:19:51,720
You’re exaggerating.

1338
02:19:52,360 --> 02:19:54,080
We’ve only been married a few days.

1339
02:19:55,400 --> 02:19:58,600
Multiply those days by five. It adds up.

1340
02:19:59,120 --> 02:20:01,240
You’re really exaggerating.

1341
02:20:02,440 --> 02:20:03,960
I get ready in five minutes.

1342
02:20:05,080 --> 02:20:06,680
Oh sure.

1343
02:20:08,720 --> 02:20:10,520
Your sense of time is… unique.

1344
02:20:11,080 --> 02:20:15,280
Your time and human time
don’t work the same.

1345
02:20:15,960 --> 02:20:17,960
-I’ve realized that. -Ha ha.

1346
02:20:20,160 --> 02:20:21,440
Where is my mascara?

1347
02:20:26,120 --> 02:20:27,680
Whatever that is, you don’t need it.

1348
02:20:40,560 --> 02:20:42,560
I mean, don’t bother looking for it.

1349
02:20:48,960 --> 02:20:51,520
Anyway, it's probably not here.

1350
02:20:51,640 --> 02:20:53,240
I'll check the room.

1351
02:21:01,200 --> 02:21:03,800
There’s something I want to do before you
go.

1352
02:21:05,920 --> 02:21:07,320
W-what is it?

1353
02:21:10,400 --> 02:21:14,520
I don’t know
how you’ll react. That’s why I’m not sure.

1354
02:21:17,640 --> 02:21:19,920
But I really want to do it.

1355
02:21:31,080 --> 02:21:32,320
Promise you won’t get mad.

1356
02:21:35,920 --> 02:21:38,760
I… can’t promise that.

1357
02:21:42,040 --> 02:21:44,960
I’ll do it anyway…

1358
02:21:45,120 --> 02:21:47,680
What are you doing? What are you doing?

1359
02:21:47,800 --> 02:21:50,440
If there are two
people in the bathroom, this has to happen.

1360
02:21:50,520 --> 02:21:52,920
You started this war. Here!

1361
02:21:54,480 --> 02:21:57,160
Stop it.

1362
02:22:14,200 --> 02:22:16,400
Say you surrender or I won’t put you down.

1363
02:22:17,520 --> 02:22:19,160
Okay, okay, stop! I surrender!

1364
02:22:19,640 --> 02:22:20,960
Not loud enough.

1365
02:22:22,000 --> 02:22:23,560
Okay, I surrender. Put me down.

1366
02:23:09,480 --> 02:23:11,080
Bless you.

1367
02:23:12,680 --> 02:23:13,800
Thank you.

1368
02:23:19,320 --> 02:23:23,080
We spent the night
outside. Of course you caught a chill.

1369
02:23:25,800 --> 02:23:27,160
Go inside and lie down.

1370
02:23:27,680 --> 02:23:31,040
Have a good rest. Wrap up well.

1371
02:23:31,680 --> 02:23:37,320
Otherwise I’ll go, and you
stay here to clean up and dry off properly.

1372
02:23:39,960 --> 02:23:41,200
Yes, I’ll go.

1373
02:23:51,000 --> 02:23:52,360
What is happening, Mercan...?

1374
02:24:10,320 --> 02:24:12,120
I told you we could’ve talked on the phone.

1375
02:24:12,280 --> 02:24:13,960
Why bring me here? Someone will see...

1376
02:24:19,640 --> 02:24:20,760
How is it, huh!?

1377
02:24:23,520 --> 02:24:28,360
Did you
like it!? Did it feel good!? How’s that!?

1378
02:24:30,200 --> 02:24:32,240
Let’s squeeze a little more…

1379
02:24:33,320 --> 02:24:38,520
You don’t
even have the breath to kill Mercan, girl!

1380
02:24:40,320 --> 02:24:42,800
I’m here!

1381
02:24:44,040 --> 02:24:46,280
Didn’t I
tell you you wouldn’t lay a hand on Mercan?

1382
02:24:46,840 --> 02:24:49,000
Didn’t I tell you you’d pay for it?!

1383
02:24:55,320 --> 02:24:56,960
Why don’t you listen!?

1384
02:25:00,360 --> 02:25:01,760
Are you… out of your mind?

1385
02:25:03,200 --> 02:25:06,600
You almost killed me…

1386
02:25:08,040 --> 02:25:10,640
If you don’t listen to me, things will get
much worse.

1387
02:25:11,280 --> 02:25:12,480
This was a rehearsal…

1388
02:25:12,560 --> 02:25:15,440
Next time I don’t stop halfway.
I go all the way, Aslı.

1389
02:25:17,400 --> 02:25:18,640
You're talking nonsense.

1390
02:25:19,400 --> 02:25:21,920
Me? Talking nonsense?

1391
02:25:23,000 --> 02:25:25,200
Drop the act. Don’t play dumb with me.

1392
02:25:25,480 --> 02:25:27,200
I know everything.

1393
02:25:28,800 --> 02:25:31,960
- I don’t understand anything.
- Oh, you understand perfectly.

1394
02:25:32,400 --> 02:25:33,760
If you go after Mercan again,

1395
02:25:33,840 --> 02:25:35,800
I’ll end you in ways
you can’t even imagine.

1396
02:25:35,920 --> 02:25:37,240
You hear me?

1397
02:25:44,120 --> 02:25:45,640
Don’t look at me like that.

1398
02:25:46,080 --> 02:25:48,080
I found out everything. You ordered it.

1399
02:25:50,280 --> 02:25:53,600
You… how… Where did you hear that?

1400
02:25:57,880 --> 02:25:59,240
I didn’t hear it from anyone.

1401
02:26:00,440 --> 02:26:03,400
I bluffed. And you fell for it.

1402
02:26:05,560 --> 02:26:08,960
Look Aslı. You’re going to do one thing.

1403
02:26:09,400 --> 02:26:11,480
You’re going to bring me information.

1404
02:26:14,280 --> 02:26:18,280
You won’t step outside
your role, or you’ll regret it.

1405
02:26:26,960 --> 02:26:29,120
I’ll make you regret it!

1406
02:26:29,840 --> 02:26:31,640
You’ll pay for this.

1407
02:26:35,280 --> 02:26:36,520
Are you okay?

1408
02:26:36,640 --> 02:26:39,840
You don’t have much time. You have to leave
before my mom sees you.

1409
02:26:39,920 --> 02:26:41,280
She’ll be here any minute.

1410
02:26:42,520 --> 02:26:44,480
I feel awful, Malik…

1411
02:26:45,240 --> 02:26:46,640
We’re finished.

1412
02:26:46,840 --> 02:26:48,600
My family won’t even look at me.

1413
02:26:49,200 --> 02:26:51,920
It’ll pass, Çiçek… It'll pass.

1414
02:26:52,640 --> 02:26:55,320
No disaster lasts forever. No night goes on
without ending.

1415
02:26:56,440 --> 02:26:59,440
-But when? -Soon, my love.

1416
02:27:00,680 --> 02:27:01,720
I promise you.

1417
02:27:02,760 --> 02:27:06,920
Your family will understand
that our love and our intentions are pure.

1418
02:27:12,440 --> 02:27:17,280
Look, I
know you can’t wear it now, but it’s yours.

1419
02:27:18,280 --> 02:27:19,920
It should stay with you.

1420
02:27:21,720 --> 02:27:26,400
You’re the only owner of this ring and of
my heart.

1421
02:27:27,320 --> 02:27:33,200
No matter what happens, I won’t give up on
you.

1422
02:27:34,160 --> 02:27:35,600
Me neither, Malik.

1423
02:27:38,000 --> 02:27:41,120
What Allah unites, people can’t tear apart.

1424
02:27:42,160 --> 02:27:44,240
I pray every night.

1425
02:27:44,960 --> 02:27:47,400
No matter what happens, I won’t give up on
us…

1426
02:27:53,160 --> 02:27:55,200
My mom’s coming, oh no.

1427
02:27:55,280 --> 02:27:57,800
Stay calm. We’re just talking.

1428
02:28:00,120 --> 02:28:03,560
She's heading toward the mansion.
Go, go, go.

1429
02:28:07,800 --> 02:28:09,360
Oh...

1430
02:28:20,680 --> 02:28:23,880
What happened? Why
are you staring at me like that?

1431
02:28:24,040 --> 02:28:26,480
Nothing, mom. Why would I stare?

1432
02:28:39,720 --> 02:28:40,960
Okay...

1433
02:28:42,000 --> 02:28:43,760
We’ll see…

1434
02:29:30,440 --> 02:29:33,720
Let me tell you something, Mother. Haydar’s
acting strange again…

1435
02:29:35,000 --> 02:29:36,520
I’m honestly disgusted by this man.

1436
02:29:37,120 --> 02:29:40,040
I don’t like the look in his eyes. It gets
under my skin.

1437
02:29:40,440 --> 02:29:43,120
That lowlife never had anything good in his
eyes.

1438
02:29:43,640 --> 02:29:45,240
Still, be careful…

1439
02:29:47,920 --> 02:29:52,120
We’re a bit distracted these days. We can’t
afford mistakes.

1440
02:29:53,680 --> 02:29:55,360
Isn’t that right, Ateş?

1441
02:29:59,440 --> 02:30:01,400
What were you saying? Couldn't hear you.

1442
02:30:04,480 --> 02:30:08,080
I feel like we’re drifting further from our
real goal every day.

1443
02:30:08,400 --> 02:30:09,440
We’re scattered.

1444
02:30:09,520 --> 02:30:12,760
And once you scatter this much, it’s hard
to pull together again…

1445
02:30:14,640 --> 02:30:20,200
We need to pull ourselves together
and strike the Yıldırıms like a fist.

1446
02:30:20,720 --> 02:30:21,840
All of them.

1447
02:30:23,200 --> 02:30:26,440
If we relax, the enemy slips in.

1448
02:30:26,920 --> 02:30:28,040
Time is running out.

1449
02:30:31,480 --> 02:30:33,240
We haven’t strayed from our goal.

1450
02:30:42,840 --> 02:30:45,560
Sweetheart… are you okay?

1451
02:30:45,720 --> 02:30:46,920
What happened, Aslı?

1452
02:30:47,000 --> 02:30:48,040
Are you alright, Aslı?

1453
02:30:48,840 --> 02:30:51,600
I'm fine. My stomach’s a little upset…

1454
02:30:51,800 --> 02:30:53,120
makes me weak.

1455
02:30:53,560 --> 02:30:55,280
But I took medicine. I’ll be fine.

1456
02:30:55,560 --> 02:30:56,760
You’ve gone pale.

1457
02:30:58,000 --> 02:31:00,560
I'll ask
them to make you some mint tea. It’ll help.

1458
02:31:02,240 --> 02:31:03,720
Take care of yourself…

1459
02:31:07,600 --> 02:31:11,400
It’s time to strike the
Yıldırıms hard, Ateş.

1460
02:31:11,960 --> 02:31:13,800
The longer we wait, the more risk we take.

1461
02:31:18,600 --> 02:31:20,640
If we can ever get a break from Mercan,

1462
02:31:22,680 --> 02:31:25,000
we’ll continue our revenge plan

1463
02:31:25,400 --> 02:31:27,680
but Her Highness
the Princess always has some crisis.

1464
02:31:28,280 --> 02:31:32,040
As you know, Ateş is
busy chasing the people who kidnapped her.

1465
02:31:32,840 --> 02:31:34,280
Someone kidnapped my wife,

1466
02:31:35,000 --> 02:31:37,120
and
I’m supposed to sit still and do nothing?

1467
02:31:38,040 --> 02:31:39,440
Is that what you expect from me?

1468
02:31:43,080 --> 02:31:44,440
Aslı’s right, Ateş.

1469
02:31:44,680 --> 02:31:46,280
Mercan takes up too much of our time.

1470
02:31:47,280 --> 02:31:48,920
Still… she might be useful.

1471
02:31:49,760 --> 02:31:51,520
Mercan is the weakest link right now.

1472
02:31:55,760 --> 02:31:57,920
We should focus on her.

1473
02:31:58,200 --> 02:32:03,000
Once she breaks, Haydar
and Nermin will panic and drop their guard.

1474
02:32:03,520 --> 02:32:06,280
Then we’ll take them down easily.

1475
02:32:07,240 --> 02:32:09,520
If we came here for revenge, let’s take it.

1476
02:32:15,680 --> 02:32:18,600
Yes, she’s the one holding them together.

1477
02:32:20,920 --> 02:32:23,920
If she falls, the rest fall too.

1478
02:32:24,680 --> 02:32:27,040
So let’s talk about
how we’re going to finish Mercan.

1479
02:32:27,120 --> 02:32:28,880
-Then... -(suddenly shouts) Enough!

1480
02:32:32,360 --> 02:32:34,200
We’ll take down Haydar, not Mercan.

1481
02:32:35,320 --> 02:32:36,520
She’s done nothing wrong.

1482
02:32:40,360 --> 02:32:42,000
She stays out of everything.

1483
02:32:42,920 --> 02:32:45,160
Not a single
hair on her head will be harmed.

1484
02:32:53,640 --> 02:32:54,840
Our target is Haydar.

1485
02:32:56,680 --> 02:32:58,080
Not Mercan.

1486
02:32:58,160 --> 02:33:00,480
-What? -What does that mean?

1487
02:33:01,600 --> 02:33:04,120
Mercan is no
longer part of the revenge plan.

1488
02:33:07,000 --> 02:33:08,400
I’m removing her from it.

1489
02:33:09,880 --> 02:33:15,000
Her name will never
again be spoken next to revenge or hatred.

1490
02:33:17,800 --> 02:33:19,040
That’s final.

1491
02:33:23,240 --> 02:33:25,320
She
is the most innocent person in this family.

1492
02:33:26,960 --> 02:33:28,640
And she is my wife.
